title: famous johnnycakes
directions: Combine sugar and salt with meal in a large mixing bowl. Scald with boiling water and stir well.
Thin immediately with milk so mixture will drop easily from spoon (additional milk may be necessary).

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream
together
eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin, then add the rest
of
the
ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured pan or Bundt pan.
Cool cake.

title: garden spot pizza
directions: Crust:
Spread crescent rolls on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate-cream drop cookies
directions: Slice each candy drop into 3 or 4 pieces and place 1 between 2 Ritz crackers.
Warm for a few minutes at a low temperature in oven until candy melts.
Delicious!

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour, mixing well.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk and set aside.
Mix together the cake mix, oleo, nuts and 1/3 cup milk.
Press half of cake mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour caramel sauce over cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Crumble the rest of the cake mixture on top and bake for 10 minutes. Let cool before cutting. Keeps best if refrigerated.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Blend with mixer.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crusts.
Makes two cheesecakes, then divide strawberry pie filling between both cheesecakes.
Let chill for 2 to 3 hours for better flavor.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each addition. In a bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped cranberries.
Spoon into 12 paper-lined 2 1/2-inch muffin cups. Fill 3/4 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add egg, salt and extract.
Mix thoroughly. Add 1 cup flour, then add all of the water.
Mix. Add remaining flour; mix. Drop by level measuring teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a floured jelly glass.
Press almond on top. Bake until brown and crisp at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 160 cookies (20 to a cookie sheet).

title: ginger cream cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, molasses and water together.
Stir in all dry ingredients until well blended.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, on cookie sheet.
Bake just until set, about 6 to 8 minutes in 400° oven.
While still warm, frost with Coffee Cream Frosting.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Heat 1 teaspoon oil in medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until softened (2 minutes).
Stir in mushrooms.
Cook until browned (about 5 minutes).
Remove mushroom mixture from skillet and set aside.
Place the remaining oil and flour in skillet.
Stir to mix.
Turn heat to low and cook, stirring constantly, until flour turns deep brown.
Still stirring, gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture thickens (about 4 minutes).
Stir in the mushroom mixture.
Add salt and pepper. Serve immediately! Serves 4.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand 24 hours.
Makes 10 servings.
This is really tasty!

title: easy caramel sauce
directions: Combine the ingredients in a small bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes or until the caramel is melted, stirring after every minute of cooking time.
Makes 1 cup.

title: fix ahead casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Mix well. Pour into 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with a lid or foil. Refrigerate all day.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture forms a ball.
Takes about 6 minutes.
Knead to form a ball after cools.
Put in airtight container.
You can divide ball and mix different food color in each.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper, then drain.
Combine the rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and remove from fire for 5 minutes.
Then serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Shape into individual balls.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, at medium speed, beat together oil, sugar and eggs until well blended. At low speed, gradually beat reserved flour mixture into egg mixture. Beat until well blended.
Stir in carrots, pineapple and pecans. Bake in preheated 350° oven.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook tiny grain pasta in boiling water according to package directions; drain, rinse in cold water and drain again.
Drain canned oranges and crushed unsweetened pineapple, reserving juices. Mix fruit with pasta in 3-quart bowl.
Pour cold juices in saucepan and add sugar, beaten eggs and flour (cornstarch).
Place over medium heat and cook, stirring until thickened.
Pour over pasta and fruit.
Stir in marshmallows.
Mix well and chill overnight. Fold in thawed whipped topping.
Makes 10 to 15 servings.
Really good and a make ahead salad/dessert.
(I never use all the juices to make the dressing.)

title: chicken monterey
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of the oil in a large skillet.
Pat the chicken dry; season them with salt and pepper and cook gently in the oil for 5 minutes.
Do not attempt to brown the chicken or it will be overcooked; it should be pale gold.
Remove chicken from skillet and reserve.
Add the onions, carrots and garlic to the oil remaining in the skillet and cook, covered, over low heat until the vegetables are tender, about 25 minutes.
Uncover the skillet and add the stock, orange juice, tomatoes and rosemary. Season to taste with salt and black pepper and simmer the mixture, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Return the chicken to the pan and simmer further, 20 to 25 minutes, or until the chicken is nearly done.
Baste the pieces with the sauce and turn them once at the 15 minute mark.

title: light orange-honey cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom and sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan with nonstick coating.
Lightly flour the pan.

title: potato starter
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Mash in water they were cooked in.
Add sugar, salt and enough cold water to make 3 1/4 cups of liquid.
Allow this mixture to become warm.
Add the yeast dissolved in 1 cup warm water.
Allow this mixture to stand overnight.
This should be light and frothy.
Pour off 1 cup to save as starter for the next baking.
Store in refrigerator in jar loosely covered.
When ready for use, set jar in warm water until 82°.
Starter should remain usable for about a week.
Work flour in this mixture as in sourdough bread.

title: peeking bonbons
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat flour and salt into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Divide butter in half.
Add red color to half and green color to other half.
Mix.
Chill 30 minutes. Shape into balls using rounded teaspoon of dough.
Refrigerate while making filling.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut up chicken and mix with green chili salsa to taste (until saucy texture).
Heat tortilla in dry skillet and then dip in cream mixture (sour cream and whipping cream).
Spoon chicken filling into shell and fold.
Lay in 9 x 11-inch glass pan.
When finished, pour remaining cream mixture over enchiladas.
Top with shredded cheese and heat at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grand champion jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add soda to milk.
Mix spices with flour.
Add flour alternately with milk, then add jam, dates, nuts, coconut and apple.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 3 layers.

title: ginger-glazed carrots
directions: Cook all ingredients except lemon juice and brown sugar in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat for 12 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until all liquid has evaporated.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Stir in lemon juice and brown sugar.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until carrots are glazed.
Low-fat and low-cholesterol.

title: instant hot tea
directions: Mix and add to water as needed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, but chili powder.
Roll in chili powder. Chill until firm.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add vanilla, lemon rind and egg. Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together; fold into creamed mixture alternately with mincemeat.
Add nuts; mix into stiff dough.
Form into rolls, wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Makes about seven dozen cookies.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix together and even out in a 9 x 13-inch pan or plastic container.
Freeze.
Take out 15 to 20 minutes before eating but return it to the freezer as soon as possible.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine reserved juice, sugar and flour in bowl; mix well.
Stir in cheese.
Add pineapple; mix well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs in small bowl. Spread over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: key-lime pie
directions: Use microwave-safe bowl and put egg yolks in microwave for 10 seconds.
Use mixer and beat egg yolks and then add sweetened condensed milk and lime juice.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine margarine and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill.
Combine brown sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into 24 balls; press into miniature muffin tins.
Fill each cup 3/4 full of brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: oven-fried cinnamon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, turmeric and pepper.
Beat egg and milk.
Coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
Combine bread crumbs and remaining flour mixture.
Dip chicken into egg; coat with crumbs.
Arrange in a roasting pan. Sprinkle with oil.
Bake until crisp and brown, about 40 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Beat with wire whisk.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Grease baking dish.
Arrange bread crumbs and raisins on the bottom.
Pour liquid mix over bread and raisins.
Usually I put cinnamon or nutmeg on top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot pennies salad
directions: Peel carrots and slice into discs.
Cook in boiling water until tender (do not overcook).
Put carrots in bowl, slice onions into thin rings and add to carrots.
Cut green pepper into strips and add to mixture; add tomato soup, undiluted.
Add vinegar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spread rice in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle all but 1 tablespoon of onion soup mix over rice.
Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Distribute mushrooms and pimentos over rice.
Add enough hot water to mushroom liquid to make 3 cups.
Pour over rice. Place browned chops on top.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon soup mix. Put in 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Should be covered with foil while baking.

title: cherry delights cookies
directions: Combine in large bowl the flour, 2 egg yolks (add some egg white), Karo syrup, sugar and margarine.
Mix, then chill for 20 minutes.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Combine first nine ingredients
in
processor and blend until smooth, about one
minute.
With
machine
running,
add both oils through feed tube
in
slow
steady stream and blend until thick. Makes about 3 cups.

title: daffodilies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 12 pieces.
With scissors, cut each piece (almost to the center) to fashion eight flower-like petals.
Indent center with tip of finger.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift into mixing bowl the flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, bananas, rolled oats and nuts; beat until thoroughly blended. Drop by teaspoons, about 1 1/2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes, or until edges are browned.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: macaroni and chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover dish and place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove casserole from refrigerator; allow to set at room temperature 1 hour.
Cook at 350° with cover for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn tamale
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 1/4 cup water in a nonstick frying pan, then mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moss ball
directions: Place cheeses in mixer bowl; let stand at room temperature until softened.
Beat on medium speed until well mixed.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll cheese mixture into 1 large ball.
Chill; roll in parsley.
Put on serving plate; chill 2 hours, or until firm. Serve the cheese ball with a variety of crackers.

title: golden chicken breast
directions: Put breasts in baking dish.
Combine mustard and vinegar in bowl until smooth; stir in preserves.
Gradually add soy sauce and stir until blended.
Pour over breasts.
Coat both sides.
Bake meaty side down 20 minutes at 325°.
Turn over and bake 40 minutes or until tender.
Brush with pan juices occasionally.

title: ceasario's homemade pizza bread
directions: In saucepan, add first 7 ingredients (except Hunt's tomato sauce).
Bring to boil.
Add Hunt's tomato sauce.
Stir, then bring to medium heat for 4 minutes.

title: mixed grill platter
directions: Cut tofu into 8 crosswise 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place on a clean kitchen towel and wrap towel around it several times.
Allow it to rest for 30 minutes.
Place tofu in a single layer in a large, shallow baking pan.
Pour half the marinade over the tofu and turn slices to coat thoroughly.
Place slices of onion on top of tofu, then top with a little of the marinade remaining.
Place vegetables on top of onions and top with the rest of the marinade. Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 3 hours.
Heat grill or broiler. Pour marinade off vegetables, reserving 1/2 cup.
Place vegetables and tofu on a rack 4-inches from the heat in batches.
Immediately combine olive oil with the 1/2 cup marinade and brush tofu and vegetables.
Turn immediately to prevent sticking, then grill until lightly browned on remaining side.
Transfer finished vegetables and tofu from grill to serving platter, and cook remaining tofu and vegetables using the same process.

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Put tenderizer on meat.
Sprinkle on cumin to your taste; it sometimes is strong.
Sprinkle on garlic powder (2 teaspoons). Put onions on meat.
Cover with salsa.
Bake at 350° until tender. Slice it and serve with flour tortillas (warm as directed on package).
Serve with Mexican rice.

title: turtles
directions: Butter 2 large nonstick cooking sheets.
Arrange pecan halves in clusters resembling turtles.
Combine cream, sugar, corn syrup, milk and butter in saucepan.
Stir on low heat until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat to high and boil without stirring until mixture turns golden, bubbles thickly and candy thermometer registers 234°, swirling pan occasionally, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop 1 tablespoon caramel onto each pecan cluster.
Melt chocolate in double boiler. Drizzle 1 tablespoon chocolate onto each candy.
Chill about 30 minutes.

title: apricot nut tea bread
directions: Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl. Beat at medium speed 1/2 minute. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly. Pour into pan (9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan, greased and floured). Bake 55 to 65 minutes at 350°. Remove from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: homemade crackers(wheat thins)
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll out onto 2 cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with salt.
Lightly roll again to press salt in.
Cut into squares or diamonds with pizza cutter.
Bake at 350°.
After 20 minutes, begin to check.
Outer ones are done first.
Remove as they turn golden brown and hard.

title: escalloped pineapple by jack brantley
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Stir thoroughly and pour in	baking	dish.
Let
set
several
hours or overnight. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Good hot or cold.

title: sour cream and chive potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in pan. Cover with water. Add salt. Cook for 25 minutes. Drain. Mash the potatoes after draining. Add sour cream, milk and margarine. Add chives and pepper. Mix well. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cracked wheat-carrot bread
directions: Put cracked wheat in small bowl.
Cover with boiling water. Let stand 15 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, mix yeast, sugar, salt and whole wheat flour.
Heat water, milk and butter until very warm.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add cracked wheat, carrots and 1/2 cup of the unbleached flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough more flour to make a firm dough.

title: low-fat quick chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: mexican style chicken
directions: Mix soups, broth and Ro-Tel in saucepan and heat to boiling. Place chicken, onion and Doritos in layers in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Pour soups over this. Crumble chips on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: moravian ginger cookies
directions: Mix molasses, shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir together remaining ingredients; blend in.
Work with hands until well blended. Cover; chill about 4 hours.
(Thorough chilling is needed to make dough hold together.)
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough out paper thin, a little at a time.
Cut in desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Frost, if desired.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell
and
cool.
In
a medium saucepan stir together the sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook
over
medium heat stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute;
remove from heat. Gradually stir
about half of the hot filling into yolks.
Return all to saucepan;
bring to a gentle boil.
Cook and stir 1 minute. Remove
from
heat.
Stir
in
butter
and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: barbecue spread
directions: Mix dressing and barbecue sauce.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, and milk. Heat on medium until boils then add butter. Let boil for 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.

title: grilled fish
directions: Brush both sides of fish with dressing and lemon juice while grilling.
Sprinkle lemon pepper on fish according to taste. Grill until done.

title: chocolate-toffee angel cake
directions: Whip the cream and fold in the grated Heath bars and fudge topping.
Split the angel food cake into three layers.
Fill and frost the cake with the whipped topping mixture.
Refrigerate until served.

title: double layer pumpkin pie(prep time: 15 minutes; refrigerating time: 4 hours.)
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust. Pour 1 cup cold milk into bowl. Add pumpkin, pudding mixes and spices. Beat with wire whisk until well mixed. (Mixture will be thick.) Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with additional Cool Whip. Makes 8 servings.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan and bring to a full boil; stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat (or until candy thermometer reaches 234°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cool at room temperature, cut.

title: creamed cabbage casserole
directions: Slice cabbage and cook until tender.
Mix soup, milk and 1/2 can French fried onions together.
Pour in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining French fried onions over top of cabbage.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox cake
directions: Roll graham crackers until fine.
Add milk and melt marshmallows, then mix graham crackers, raisins and nuts together and pour over marshmallows and mix well.
Place in pan, lined with waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Pour the 2 cups of boiling water over first four ingredients and cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast, sugar and warm water and add to first mixture.
Next add the flour.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and shape into loaves.
Let rise to double again.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
While warm, use butter knife to punch holes in cake.
Pour eagle brand milk and cream of coconut on top of warm cake.
When completely cool, spread cool whip on top of cake.
Sprinkle shredded coconut on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: kevin's oreo dessert
directions: Crumble 1/2 package Oreo cookies and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix oleo, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
In another bowl, mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Combine and pour over crumbled Oreo cookies.
Crumble remaining cookies and sprinkle on top of dessert.
Freeze until firm.

title: buttercream icing(decorating)
directions: With an electric mixer, cream butter and shortening.
In separate bowl, sift powdered sugar; measure.
Add powdered sugar to creamed mixtures.
Add vanilla, salt and milk.
Mix until smooth.
You may need to thin a little if too thick (should be the consistency of mashed potatoes).

title: light cheesecake
directions: Mix
cream
cheese, Cool Whip, vanilla and lemon juice. Pour in crust and let chill for at least 2 hours.

title: pork steak casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Cook noodles and drain.
Drain sauerkraut.
Mix in casserole meat, noodles, sauerkraut and soup. Bake 1/2 to 1 hour at 350°.
(If too dry, add a little milk.)

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Heat oleo, shortening, water and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well. Beat eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt shortening in water and add to flour, sugar and cocoa. Put soda in buttermilk; stir.
Then add with eggs and vanilla to first mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf or angel food cake pan for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: raw potato dumplings(kartoflane kluski)
directions: Grate potatoes; drain off brown liquid.
Add beaten eggs, salt, crumbs and flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop into boiling water from a wet spoon.
Dumpling should be 1 1/2-inches long when cooked.
They're done when they float to the top.
Saute onion in skillet (low flame).
Add dumplings and simmer for a few minutes.

title: chili chicken
directions: Mix chicken and tomato sauce in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans and corn. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Prepare dumplings.
Drop by 12 spoonfuls onto hot chili.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook about 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry mix up
directions: In pan, spread cherry filling; top with pineapple and pour in dry cake mix.
Mix with fork.
Mash out lumps.
Add nuts; add cold butter in pats.
Place evenly over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 46 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Use at least 2 teaspoons in 1 cup boiling water.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Put batter in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen cranberry banana salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a medium bowl; set pineapple aside. Add bananas to the juice.
In a large bowl, combine cranberry sauce and sugar.
Remove bananas, discarding juice, and add to cranberry mixture.
Stir in pineapple, whipped topping and nuts. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Freeze until solid.
Remove from the freezer 15 minutes before cutting.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients about 3 to 4 minutes.
Place in greased and prepared pan.
Bake at 375° until done, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Remove from pan.
Top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind up Oreo cookies and set aside.
Combine cream cheese, margarine and sugar and set aside.
Combine pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese mixture and layer with Oreo cookies in flower pot.
Add artificial flowers and serve with a garden trowel.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Combine sugar and water in large heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add nuts and flavoring.
Cook on medium heat; stir constantly, until mixture is dry and peanuts are sugar-coated and crystallized.
Place in flat pan and bake in 250° oven about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, checking every 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: gumbo
directions: Boil the chicken until thoroughly done.
Remove skin and meat off the bone (except for wings, leave intact).
Dice meat into bite size chunks.
Note when boiling chicken, season water well. Save approximately 2 to 3 cups stock depending on amount of gumbo you make.
Drain remaining stock.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Add flour to onion mixture. Add 1/2 of the Velveeta to onion-flour mixture. Add the eggs to the broccoli; mix well. Combine rice, soup, broccoli, and cheese mixture. Fold in last 1/2 of Velveeta. Put into buttered casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, spices and salt.
Combine molasses, lard, butter and water in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients to liquid; blend well.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Turn onto well floured bread board.
Using well floured rolling pin, roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in 375° oven 12 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: non-cook cookies
directions: Boil oleo, sugar and milk for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Place on waxed paper.
Let air dry until hard.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream the cheese and butter. Combine flour and red pepper. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Shape dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness. Brush wafers with beaten egg.
Top each wafer with pecan half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: barb's marbled cheesecake deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust.
Stir together margarine and cocoa until smooth.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, then flour.
Measure 1 1/2 cups batter into medium bowl.
Beat in cocoa mixture.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cut out core.
Put meat mixture in center of cabbage leaf.
Roll up and toothpick rolls together, if needed.
Pour can of stewed tomatoes over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: curry chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except the chicken pieces in a casserole or roaster.
Mix thoroughly to blend spices.
Add chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour or until chicken and rice are tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: choco-caramel cake
directions: Mix caramels, milk, and margarine. Cover low heat until melted. Mix cake as directed on label. Grease and flour a 13 x 9 in. pan and pour in one half of cake batter. Cook in 350 oven for 15 minutes. Spread caramel mixture over hot cake and sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips. Cover with the remaining cake batter. Bake for 20 minutes in oven
at 250. Then raise oven temperature to 350 and bake
10 minutes longer.

title: birthday cake icing
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add Crisco, powdered sugar, water, and flavoring.
Beat until desired spreading consistency.

title: fruit cake
directions: Use two 9 x 5-inch pans. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
For an angel cake pan, bake 2 1/2 hours.

title: diviinty
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage.
Add half of hot mixture to egg whites and beat until cool.
Let remaining syrup cool until it forms hard ball in cold water.
Add to egg white mixture, and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan; spread 1 inch thick.
Cut into squares.

title: trinity baked chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, soy sauce, ginger and pepper; pour over chicken in shallow baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 15 minutes.
Arrange fruit about chicken.
Baste with liquid and bake 10 minutes.

title: cube steak and gravy
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown both sides.
Place in crock-pot. Mix gravy mix and pour over steak.
Cook all day on low, or until steak is tender.

title: snowballs
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together for 10 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Combine with remaining ingredients (all but coconut).
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into shredded coconut and hand roll into balls. Yields 36 snowballs.

title: fall harvest rice
directions: Cook sausage in skillet, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Combine sausage, rice, apple, onion, celery, raisins, sugar, salt, allspice, cinnamon and pepper.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma's homemade cider
directions: Place spices in tea ball.
Put with rest of ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn on high for 30 minutes, then on low until ready to serve.
Remove spices after a couple of hours.

title: no bake oatmeal fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter, milk and cocoa for 3 minutes; stir while boiling.
Take pan off stove and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Drop on wax paper.

title: quick, tasty pork chops
directions: Wash center cut pork chops.
Rub thoroughly on both sides with salt and pepper to taste; place in foil covered shallow pan. Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce on each side of the chops.
Rubbing it in and turning every 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in slow cooker or bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat 10 minutes and put into tube pan.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream well butter and cheese; add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake on ungreased sheet at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Start on bottom rack; move up last 5 minutes.

title: elegant chicken crepes
directions: In a saucepan, combine onion and water.
Cook; cover 5 minutes.
Do not drain.
Combine milk, cornstarch, salt and pepper; add to onion.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese mixture.
Add mushrooms to remaining cheese mixture; cover and set aside.

title: barbecued limas
directions: Fry diced bacon. Add chopped onion, chopped pepper, sugar, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and chopped garlic. Simmer 10 minutes. Add drained beans. Bake in casserole for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: anna's delight twists
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, shortening or olive oil, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix yeast with flour mixture.
Cover with plastic; cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
It rises.
Take out half of dough.
Roll it out flat, sprinkle with sugar.
Repeat 2 more times.
Cut flattened dough in half and then into strips and twist.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt shortening.
Add flour; stir until it is brown.
Lower heat.
Add shrimp and cook about 3 minutes, or until pink.
Add garlic, onion, parsley and bell pepper; cook 2 minutes longer. Raise heat.
Gradually add water, then remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, then simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot over rice.
Serves 4.
Very good!

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Fold in chopped cherries.
Pour into tube pan and place in cold oven.
Bake for 2 hours at 275°.
Cool on rack about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Mix together the following ingredients for Cherry Frosting and frost cold cake.

title: new potato salad
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes; reduce heat to medium.
Slice into bite size pieces (unpeeled).
Mix oil and next 7 ingredients.
Add potatoes and celery.
Toss to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: deer steak and gravy
directions: Roll deer steaks in flour and brown.
Pour favorite soup over steak.
Add mushrooms. Bake all this in oven until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Place beans, onion rings and almonds in layers in casserole. Fry bacon crisp.
Mix sugar and vinegar with drippings.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over beans.
Let marinate overnight.
Crumble bacon on top.
Heat at 350° until piping hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese boxes
directions: Melt oleo and cheese over low heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cheese mixture, beating until blended.
Stack 3 slices of bread, trim off crust.
Spread each layer and top with cheese mixture.
Cut stacks into 4 boxes.
Spread cheese mixture thinly around edges and top like icing.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 28 to 30.
Freeze and remove and bake as directed.

title: fan's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add salt and flavorings.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: choco-holic brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Nestle Choco Bake.
Cool to room temperature.

title: warm and spicy autumn punch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Stud the whole oranges with cloves and bake for 30 minutes. In a large saucepan, combine the apple juice and cinnamon stick. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the nutmeg, honey, lemon juice and pineapple juice. Serve hot in a punch bowl with the 2 clove-studded baked oranges floating on top.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Start by preheating oven to 350°. Fill a large pan halfway with water and stick in oven while waiting for bread pudding to be mixed. You will need a 10 x 10 x 2-inch pan to put bread pudding in.

title: nickelodeon cake
directions: Cook in oven 20 minutes just a little bit hot.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well.
Freeze.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop up raw cabbage.
Add oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Make ahead, good next day.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stir to coat.
Place on baking sheets and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: fennel chews
directions: Beat butter, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Add vanilla, fennel and nuts.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Dough will be thick and a bit difficult to spread.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until just tender; drain well. Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots. Cool and put in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix both cans of sauce in a bowl. Pour a little of the mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan, enough to just coat.
Reserve remainder.
In a heavy skillet, brown the meat.
Add taco seasoning and water per package directions.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Dice onion.
Shred cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, saving some cheese and crackers for topping. Place into a casserole dish.
Top with the rest of the cheese and crackers.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: raspberry frost
directions: Be sure pineapple juice and ginger ale are chilled.
Combine 1/4 of juice, sherbet and ginger ale in blender, until light and frothy, about one minute.
Pour into large punch bowl.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Stir in undrained thawed raspberries.

title: half-cup pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice well.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: peanut butter pie(children love this pie.  so do adults!)
directions: Mix well peanut butter, powdered sugar, cream cheese and milk. Pour into graham cracker crust, and sprinkle nuts on top.
When sliced for serving, dip large tablespoon of Cool Whip on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: fried bean cakes
directions: To beans, add enough self-rising flour to make the mix thick. Add pepper to taste.
Fry in enough oil on medium heat until brown on both sides.

title: summertime drink
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Layer 6 tortillas (having been dipped in hot chicken stock), half of chicken and sprinkle with garlic and chili powder according to taste.
Add half of bell pepper and onion.
Repeat layers.

title: broccoli-pecan salad
directions: Break or cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add nuts, raisins, onion and bacon bits.

title: honey-glazed chicken
directions: In a bowl or bag, combine flour, salt and cayenne pepper; add chicken pieces and dredge or shake to coat.
Pour 4 tablespoons butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; place chicken in pan, turning pieces once to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, honey, lemon juice, soy sauce, curry powder and remaining butter; pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes more or until chicken is tender, basting several times with pan drippings.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute grated onion in melted butter.
Alternate layers of cooked carrots, grated cheese and sauteed onion.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: barbara's back porch rolls
directions: Put Crisco, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Pour in boiling water and stir.
Add beaten eggs and stir well.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add Crisco mixture.
Gradually stir in 6 cups unsifted flour.
Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and cut with a 2-inch cutter.
Put in greased muffin tins and let rise until double, about 3 or 4 hours.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 7 or 9 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pea fritters
directions: Prepare skillet with shortening or oil for frying.
Mash peas with a fork and add egg, flour, pepper and salt.
Stir, then drop with tablespoon in patties in skillet.
Fry on medium to low heat until brown on each side.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° to 345° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Dip into beaten eggs and coat with meal and flour mixture.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in frying pan.
Fry cucumbers, turning occasionally, until tender.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add walnuts, then eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Combine both corns and sour cream.
Pour into butter.
Sprinkle corn bread mix over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: purple monster
directions: Put milk, berries, sugar and 1 pint of vanilla ice cream in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
Pour into glasses and top with a scoop of ice cream.
Garnish with fresh blueberries.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: custard
directions: In heavy saucepan, scald 3 cups milk (do not boil).
In a bowl, beat	together
the
eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat well, then stir in the
cup
of cold milk.
Add some of the hot milk to the mixture.
Mix
well,
then gradually add to the rest of the hot milk.
Cook
over
just medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture coats
the back of the spoon (do not overcook or let boil).
Strain.
Add
teaspoon
of
vanilla.
Best
if allowed to ripen in refrigerator or until next day.

title: the best carrot cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine with liquids. Beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Add carrots, nuts and raisins and mix to blend.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
(I use one 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Do not open oven door during baking time.
Frost with cream cheese icing when cold.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Combine banana and yogurt in bowl; stir to mix.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with banana mixture until all is blended together.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in greased pans 1/2 full and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Yields 3 small loaves.

title: lemon ice box pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.
Serve when chilled.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and let dry.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar and egg yolk; real well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. After baking, place Hershey bars on baked crust.
Spread when Hershey bars are melted and sprinkle top with nuts.

title: chunky vegetables over shells
directions: In large pot, combine all ingredients except shells.
Simmer over low heat until carrots are tender (about 30 minutes).
Serve over cooked shells.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salad dressing and vanilla together.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in warm water.
Bake in a greased baking pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak smothered with onions
directions: Coat surface of steak with a mixture of flour, salt, marjoram and pepper.
Brown steak well on both sides in hot shortening in a large frypan with close fitting cover.
Sprinkle any remaining flour mixture over steak.
Add 1 cup of onions and the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining onions.
Cover; continue cooking until meat is fork-tender, about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix in flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add zucchini and nuts. Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Very good with cream cheese that has been thinned a little with milk and powdered sugar.

title: zucchini cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook zucchini until tender.
Mix all ingredients and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Add sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly with mixture. Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze until firm.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, ham, salt and pepper.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Other ingredients may be added, such as peppers, mushrooms, bacon, etc.
Makes 2 pies.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, taco seasoning and spread in bottom of platter of pan (approximately 13 x 9-inch).
Top with lettuce, onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream eggs, shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: morning glory muffins(375~ oven)
directions: Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin tins or use paper liners.
Mix cereal and milk in large bowl; let stand 5 minutes or until softened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill tins almost full.
Bake for 22 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from pans.

title: creamy dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Serve with Australian Outback Salad or fresh fruit salad.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken (skin and remove fat) in salted water with bay leaf until tender.
Remove from broth, throw away bay leaf. Remove bones and cut or tear meat into pieces; set aside.
In very large bowl or pan, crumble cornbread and white bread; add seasoning, chicken broth and soup.
Mix thoroughly.
If too dry, add the can of water.
Mix in chicken.
Generously grease 3-quart baking dish or roaster pan.
Put dressing in pan.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: orange chocolate balls
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add the chocolate and melt over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
In a bowl beat the sugar and continue beating until light and creamy.
Add the chocolate mixture and the orange rind and pecans.
Put the mixture in the refrigerator.
Chill until set and easy to handle. With two spoons, roll the mixture into balls.
Place chocolate sprinkles on a piece of waxed paper.
Roll the chocolate balls in sprinkles until covered.
Let chocolate balls firm up in the refrigerator before serving.

title: cranberry broccoli salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, combine cranberries, broccoli, cabbage, walnuts, raisins, onion and bacon. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cranberry mixture. Toss well. Cover and refrigerate for up to 24 hours. Serve on leafy lettuce. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: You will need a graham cracker crust in a pie plate.
Spoon softened rainbow sherbet into shell and freeze hard.
Top with 1 small carton of Cool Whip.
Add candy sprinkles or shaved chocolate for color.
Freeze.
Slice and serve.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Break chicken into pieces and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix both cans of soup with 1/2 cup milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the chicken. Cover with Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Combine melted margarine with 1/2 cup of chicken broth and pour over top of stuffing.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams; place aside.
Add reserved juice gradually to clams and cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco, seasoned salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.

title: pumpkin bars with cream cheese frosting
directions: Butter and flour 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 25 minutes.
When cool, frost with cream cheese frosting.
May be frozen up to 6 months.

title: hermit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Sift flour and cinnamon twice, leaving enough to flour fruit.
Add nuts.
Put in vanilla and bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine cream, flour, salt, paprika, garlic powder, pepper and onion. Arrange one cup of potatoes in the bottom of a two qt casserole dish, cover with 1/3 of the cream mixture and dot with 1/3 of the butter. Top with two more layers of potatoes and cream mixture. Then pour the boiling water over the top of the layers. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hr or until potatoes are tender.

title: sirloin kabobs
directions: Cut bacon into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Thread skewers with sirloin, bacon and mushrooms caps.
Repeat until skewers are full. Marinate in dressing for 2 or 3 hours at room temperature, turning frequently.
Cook over charcoal grilled to desired doneness.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all together in a cake pan.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine sugars and sour cream in large saucepan.
Cover over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking without stirring to 234° on candy thermometer or until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir gently until all nuts are cooked. Pour on wax paper.
Separate nuts with fork.
Let dry; store in airtight container.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.
Place in boiling water and cook 5 minutes to soften slightly.
Drain.
In large kettle, place potatoes, cream-style corn and oleo.
Add evaporated milk and whole milk.
Cook on medium to low heat until oleo is melted and milk is warm.
Don't boil.
Stir occasionally to avoid sticking.

title: wilda's sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in fat; add water, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Drain pineapple and save syrup.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce; add to pork.
Mix cornstarch well with pineapple juice and add.
Continue cooking, stirring until gravy thickens. Add pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes and serve over rice with soy sauce.

title: jelled cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water. Add the cranberry sauce and pineapple and stir until well mixed. Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13 inch glass baking dish. Place in the refrigerator until slightly thickened, about 30

minutes. Remove from the refrigerator and stir in the pecans. Place back in the refrigerator for at least 3 hours, or overnight, before serving. Cut into 12 servings and use a spatula to remove. Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 8 minutes in boiling water.
Drain.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and egg with broccoli.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dip chicken in egg, milk and bread crumbs.
Brown lightly in olive oil.
Remove chicken and set aside. Make gravy with flour and butter.
When bubbly, add wine and water.
May need to add more water to get to right consistency.
Squeeze in lemon juice. Add chicken to gravy. Slice lemons on top.
Add salt and garlic. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta.
Soooo Good!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix carrots, sugar, eggs, vegetable oil and nuts by hand.
Mix well and add the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix all by hand; do not beat.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes in a well-greased cake pan.
Cool well and ice with cream cheese icing.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine. Combine remainder of ingredients, except for topping and mix well.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with bread and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If mixed ahead of time and refrigerated, increase baking time to 10 to 15 minutes. Extra rice and grated cheese may be added.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Saute onion in oleo in microwave.
Crumble bread crumbs.
Add onion, oleo, eggs, chicken, soup and seasonings. Add enough broth to make it fairly soupy.
Can use canned broth or instant bouillon and water.
Cook in crock-pot on low 4 hours.

title: chocolate chip mint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Stir in flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in mint chips.

title: portuguese beans
directions: Slice and saute linguica; add sirloin.
Pour off fat.
Saute onion, mushrooms, bell pepper and garlic.
Add to meat and let simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In a large slow cooker or stew pot, add all ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add 5 to 6 slices of bacon in the last hour.

title: spiced ham rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let marinate overnight. Freeze rolls so that they are hard and slice them lengthwise like a big sandwich bun.
Spread mustard mixture on bottom of rolls. Layer Swiss cheese, ham, more cheese, etc.
Spread rest of mustard mixture on underside of rolls.
Spread a little mixture on top of sandwich.
Cover with foil; bake about 15 minutes at 300°. Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Slice into individual sandwiches.
They stay together better if you leave them in the foil pan the rolls came in.

title: marinated fruit
directions: Combine fruit.
Combine liquids and pour over fruit.
Chill for two hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat margarine and sugar in a large bowl till smooth and add applesauce, eggs and milk and beat till smooth.
Add bananas and beat at low speed.
Then beat at high speed 1 to 2 minutes.

title: googy cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar and pour over top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese in a bread bowl
directions: Hollow out the loaf of bread, reserving as much as possible to slice thin for the dip.
Saw-tooth the crust as you would a watermelon.

title: beef stroganoff with rice and potatoes
directions: Cut meat in small strips (cuts easier if frozen).
Sprinkle meat with seasonings.
Brown meat in heavy skillet with shortening or oil.
Stir in mushroom soup and 1 cup of beef broth.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add onions and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: cranberry-apple punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Chill all ingredients.
Stir together in large punch bowl.
Makes 60 servings.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Set aside 1 cup of Chow Mein Noodles. Mix remaining ingredients, mix well. Put in 10x6x1 1\2 baking dish.
Sprinkle with cup of chow mein noodles. Bake at 375° for 30 min.

title: apples and cheese
directions: Pour apples into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Melt together margarine and Velveeta cheese, then add sugar.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Add to apples.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and browning, approximately 30 minutes.

title: quick cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients except the pasta.
Bring to a boil in a skillet.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: potato casserole
directions: Prepare instant potatoes for 6 servings.
Add cream, egg, chopped onion and sour cream.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Combine ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: dole golden sauce for ham
directions: In saucepan, combine juice and remaining ingredients.
Heat until it boils and thickens.
Add pineapple slices.
Heat through. Spoon over cooked ham or chicken.

title: date balls(no bake)
directions: Melt oleo and sugar together.
Add dates and bring to a boil. Add eggs and milk to date mixture and boil for 2 minutes.
Cool slightly (15 minutes), then add Rice Krispies, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Cool.
Form into balls when you are able to roll them in your hand.
Roll in flaked or shredded coconut.

title: french mustard
directions: Cook all ingredients until thickens.
Mix with ground ham or any meat.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Add cocoa and vanilla.
Put red cake coloring in buttermilk.
Add slowly with flour.
Put vinegar in soda and add last.
Make 3 layers and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and onion in water to make broth.
When done, remove chicken from bones and add to broth.

title: dump cake
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer the pineapple and pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over cherries.
Over cake mix, sprinkle pecans. Cut margarine into patties and place on top of nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip, ice cream or just plain.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Pour 2 cups batter into pan and bake 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and margarine in saucepan and remove from heat.
Add milk and mix well.
Spread caramel mixture evenly over cake.
Spread remaining cake batter over caramel mixture.
Top with nuts.
Return cake to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool and serve.

title: mushroom roll-ups
directions: Peel mushrooms and dice, then saute for five minutes in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and Accent.
Stir in cream and simmer until thick.
Add chives and lemon juice.
Blend well. Remove crusts from bread and roll slices thin.
Spread with mushroom mixture and roll up.
Pack and freeze if desired.
When ready to serve, defrost; cut each roll in half and toast on all sides in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter until tender. Combine broccoli, soup and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Add sauteed vegetables to broccoli mixture, stirring well.
Serve hot.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil white potatoes, cool and cut in small cubes.
Chop celery, onions and green pepper very fine.
Combine all ingredients with salad dressing and mix with potatoes.
Garnish with paprika.

title: white sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well; put into casserole dish and sprinkle coconut lightly on top.
Put small marshmallows on top and brown lightly.
Use more or less pecans, raisins and coconut, as you like.

title: peter pan cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, salt and peanut butter; mix well.
Add granulated sugar and brown sugar gradually and cream thoroughly. Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Stir in flour and soda, blending well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Press cookies lightly with a fork.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spaghettini bolognese
directions: Saute mushrooms, carrot, garlic, onion, celery and green pepper in Wesson oil in Dutch oven.
Add sausage; cook until sausage loses redness.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghettini.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: french potato salad
directions: Put potatoes in serving bowl.
Mix all other ingredients very well, then drizzle over potatoes.
Gently stir until all potatoes are covered with dressing.
May be served warm or cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beef dish
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 5 to 6 hours.
After sour cream.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger until done in skillet.
Peel and slice potatoes about 1/3-inch thick.
Mix enough water with soup to make 3 cups.
Open and drain beans.
Put a layer of potatoes, green beans, salt and half of hamburger.
Repeat layer.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue meat
directions: Roast sesame seed in frying pan until brown.
Remove from heat and crush.
Mix seed, wine and onions in bowl with sliced meat and let stand for 1 hour or more.
Put meat on grill until cooked.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Put chicken in crock-pot.
Add soup and water.
Cook on high for about 8 hours.

title: mixed nut candy
directions: Cook sugar and butter to 300° or until the mixture turns brown. Spread mixed nuts in jelly roll pan.
Pour cooked mixture over nuts.
Top with chocolate chips.
Spread with wooden spoon.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: fail proof rolls
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and hot water; add cold water, salt and eggs.
In small bowl, mix yeast, warm water and salt.
Add to first mix; add flour and mix well.
Cover with cloth (wet).
Refrigerate; let rise until double in height.
Take out and make rolls.
Brush with melted butter.
Rise 1 hour or until doubles in size.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Put ingredients into saucepan and cook over medium heat until hot.
Put crushed chips, shredded Monterey Jack cheese and chopped avocado (optional) into serving bowl and ladle soup over it.

title: pecan molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, molasses and egg.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture, then add butterscotch morsels.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place in sprayed cookie pan.
Top with pecan and bake at 370° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix and place on large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts and butterscotch bits.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and trim broccoli; cut stalks into spears.
Cook broccoli, covered in a small amount of boiling unsalted water about 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add evaporated milk, sugar, whole milk and vanilla. (If adding fruit, process in blender and add to mixture.)
Freeze in electric or crank freezer.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together use 1/4 to 1/2 cup mix for each cup. Pour boiling water
over mix.

title: french fried carrots
directions: Peel and cut in half; drop in hot grease in "Fry Daddy" or deep fryer.
Cook as you would French fried potatoes.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Mix together chicken, cheese, celery, pineapple, nuts, paprika, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Pile in a baked pie crust.
Pillsbury's ready to bake crust is good.
Frost top with 1 cup Cool Whip and garnish with grated carrots.
Chill until serving time.
Serves 6.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown ground venison; drain.
Mix all ingredients in slow cooker.
Add garlic salt, pepper and chili powder to your own taste.
Cook for several hours in slow cooker.

title: diabetic easter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add evaporated milk and stir for 2 to 3 minutes, then add vanilla and sweetener. Spread on small foil pan or plate.
Chill.
Cut into 8 small pieces.
Form into egg shaped ball and roll lightly in pudding powder or nuts.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Season ribs with seasoned salt and pepper.
Roast in shallow covered pan about 1 hour at 375°.
Drain off fat.
Make spaghetti sauce mix as directed on package, using tomato sauce and omit oil. Add remaining ingredients; simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over ribs; continue roasting, uncovered, about 1 hour at 350°.
Baste several times.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: the natural tomato sauce
directions: Saute onions and pepper to juice of tomatoes in saucepan and bring to boil.
Let simmer until reduced about half in volume. Cut tomatoes in small pieces or mash and add with seasoning to juice.
Let simmer briefly.
(Should be quite thick.)
Serve over patties.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put all of the ingredients in bowl and mix with hands.
Make into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: nell reynold's molasses cookies
directions: From Harriet Look's cookbook.

title: chunky artichoke salsa
directions: Drain marinade from artichokes.
Chop artichokes with onion, olives and tomatoes.
Add garlic, basil, salt and pepper and stir. Chill and serve.
Makes 2 cups.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay dough on cookie sheet, joined together, making a crust. Bake according to package directions.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise with mixer.
Spread on top of crust.
Prepare vegetables and arrange on top of crust with dressing.
Add cheese.
Refrigerate 1 hour before cutting into pieces.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt into mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until it is a very fine crumb.
Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls about the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Flatten each with bottom of a small glass tumbler covered with a dampened cloth.
(Or you may first dip the bottom of the tumbler in oil and then in sugar.)
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown.
Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, sugar and vegetable oil.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Add pumpkin and beat into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cool cookie-wiches
directions: Prepare a batter for a white cake.
Bake as small drop cakes. Cool.
Cover with white icing.
Roll in coconut.

title: mexican chicken kiev
directions: Put chicken between 2 pieces of wax paper and pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Put 2 tablespoons chiles and 1 strip cheese in center of each chicken piece.
Roll up and tuck ends under. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, chili powder, salt, cumin and pepper.
Roll each stuffed chicken piece in shallow bowl containing melted butter.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place chicken rolls seam side down in baking dish and drizzle with little melted butter.
Cover and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cute cheese cake cups
directions: You will also need 2-inch round foil baking cups.

title: holiday double onion stuffing
directions: In large skillet, brown bacon lightly.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add apples and celery; cook until tender. Remove from heat.
Add onions, stuffing and almonds and mix well. Mix eggs, water, thyme and broth.
Pour over stuffing and mix well.
Spoon into 8 x 12-inch greased pan or baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then add Durkee onions to top of stuffing.
Bake 5 minutes and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: bundt pan bread
directions: Take the biscuits and stand them up around the sides of the Bundt pan.
Pour the oleo over the top and sides of the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Pulls apart for slices.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over dates, soda and butter.
Let stand until cool.
Add egg, flour, sugar, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased and floured 12 x 7-inch pan.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto a hot greased griddle.
Cook about 5 minutes or until brown; turn once to brown other side.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Stir in soup and wine.
Heat through. Stir in mushrooms and shrimp.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with Parmesan.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: fun milk
directions: Or use 2 teaspoons sweetened Kool-Aid.
Omit sugar and water. Increase milk to 1 cup.

title: country ham steak with glazed apples
directions: In skillet, melt margarine until sizzling.
Stir in brown sugar and mustard.
Add apples.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir occasionally until apples are crisply tender.
Place ham in skillet with apples on top.
Cover.
Cook until ham is heated through.

title: banana bread*
directions: Cream shortening and eggs.
Dissolve soda in mashed bananas and add together.
Add nuts, sugar, flour and salt.
Place in greased bread pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
On a cookie sheet, place slightly flattened biscuit.
Top with about 2 teaspoons pizza sauce, then add a couple shreds of cheese and your other toppings.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: indian corn
directions: Brown beef and drain grease.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pickled fish
directions: Mix sauce (the first 6 ingredients) in large kettle and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Cool sauce.
Rinse fish and dry.
Sprinkle lime juice over fish slices and season with salt.
Flour both sides lightly when ready to fry.
Heat olive oil with crushed garlic in frypan.
Remove garlic as soon as it browns.
Fry fish slices on low heat 15 minutes.
Remove and arrange in deep glass dish.
Pour sauce over it.
Cover; refrigerate at least 24 hours. Serve cold.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar; make a well.
Add oil, yolks and liquid; beat well with a spoon.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff.
Fold egg yolk mixture over egg whites.
Gently fold until blended.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Invert; cool.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add sugar mixture, one cup at a time.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla, cinnamon and pears.
Spoon into a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or a little longer.

title: shelley's broccoli casserole
directions: Pour cooked broccoli in a baking dish. Put velveeta cheese chunks and crushed crackers over broccoli. Drizzle melted butter over everything.

title: pork chops with amber rice
directions: Brown pork chops in heavy skillet; season with salt and pepper.
Place
rice
in a 12 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange
juice
over rice.
Arrange browned pork chops on rice. Pour
soup
over
all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Flatten the biscuits, 1 at a time.
Put a hot dog on biscuit. Bring edges up to cover hot dog.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Serve with mustard, ketchup or relish.

title: go go salad
directions: Mix all fruits together and serve cold.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup of strawberries.
Mix with sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually until smooth. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Add red food coloring (if desired).
Cool.
Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup
for garnish.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm (3 hours).
Top with Cool Whip; garnish with berries.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.

title: frosty pudding milkshake
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add pudding mix and ice cream; cover. Blend at high speed 30 seconds.
Scrape sides of container; blend 30 seconds longer.
Pour into glasses.
Top with club soda.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy chocolate squares
directions: Arrange 15 graham squares on bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Beat cream cheese in bowl until smooth. Gradually beat in 1 cup milk until blended. Add remaining milk and pudding mix. Beat for 2 minutes. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread half the pudding mixture over graham squares. Top with remaining graham squares and pudding mix. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: potato breakfast casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skin until tender.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices. In buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish, cover bottom with potato slices.
Cover with layer of crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with onions and then cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over layered pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and condensed milk. Sprinkle Kool-Aid on top and stir until firm. Put in baked pie shell and refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until done; drain. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, grate potatoes. Mix with other ingredients.
Place in shallow 2 quart baking dish and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup of cookies and rocks* into the pudding mixture.
Spoon onto pie crust.
Sprinkle remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours.
Garnish with gumdrop flowers or gummie worms.

title: veal cacciatore
directions: Brown veal, add seasonings, cover and let simmer for about 1 hour.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms and peas.
Cook over low heat, turning occasionally until tender.

title: two-step batter fried chicken
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix egg, milk and 1 tablespoon corn oil.
Add to flour mixture and beat.
Dip chicken into batter, coating completely. Drain.
Pour corn oil into deep fryer or 3-quart saucepan.
Heat oil to 375°.
Carefully add chicken, a few pieces at a time. Fry about 4 minutes; drain. Place in a shallow baking pan and bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer 1:
French onion dip, Ranch mix and cream cheese, mixed.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon in bowl.
Stir in nuts.
Mix vanilla, eggs, oil, bananas and pineapple in bowl. Add to flour mixture; mix just until moistened.
Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Pan may be prepared with nonstick baking spray.
May substitute 2 loaf pans for Bundt pan.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop onions and tomato.
Pit and remove pulp from avocados. Add onions, tomato and lemon juice to avocado pulp.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fill container, then finish filling with whole milk to make a gallon. Freeze in gallon freezer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, salt and allspice; set aside.
Cream eggs, oil, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Add grated zucchini and vanilla; mix well. Add dry ingredients and chopped nuts.
Mix.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 250° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: italian sesame seed bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar; set aside 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Add salt, oil and 3 tablespoons sesame seed. Stir in flour slowly until a stiff dough forms.
Turn on lightly floured board.
Knead 10 minutes, until dough is smooth and satiny. Cut into 4 pieces.
Shape or cut each piece into 3 parts about 30-inches long.
Braid.
Place braid in tight coil on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until doubled.

title: pinto bean cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put by tablespoonfuls into skillet of hot grease.
Turn with egg turner until brown.

title: hearty beef pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spoon stew into a 2-quart round casserole bowl.
Place pie crust on top of the stew.
Fold edges under. Sprinkle with cheese; cut 2 or 3 slits in crust.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.
(Use as much cheese as desired.)

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients together with enough cracker crumbs to form patties.
Roll in cornmeal and fry in Crisco until golden brown.

title: texas brownies
directions: Combine butter, shortening and coffee in saucepan (1 cup water plus 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa may be substituted for coffee). Bring to a boil.
Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Pour boiling mixture over. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well and spread on well buttered cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except shrimp.
Add shrimp and combine.
Add a little more ketchup, if needed, for slightly pink color.
Allow time for flavors to mix.
Serve with crackers.

title: chile rellenos
directions: In a 9 x 14-inch pan, put a layer of Monterey Jack, then 1/2 can chilies, next a layer of Cheddar cheese, then the rest of the chilies.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Add Bisquick and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl combine the eggs, sugar, salt, dark corn syrup, maple syrup and vanilla.
Beat well with an electric mixer or wire whip.

title: chocolate rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler over hot water.
Combine Marshmallow Creme and rum flavoring in small bowl.
Stir into chocolate; mix well.
Add cereal, coconut and pecans, mixing well. Form into small balls.
Roll in additional coconut or chopped pecans.
Chill until firm.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: vanilla-butter sugar cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar and butter; beat until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture until completely blended.
Chill for 30 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to a 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with holiday cutters dipped in flour. Using a floured spatula, transfer cookies to ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: frozen pudding treats
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into 6 (5 ounce) paper cups.
Insert wooden or plastic spoon into each for a handle.
Press a square of aluminum foil or wax paper down onto pudding to cover, piercing center of foil with handle.
Freeze until firm, at least 5 hours. Press firmly on bottom of cup to release pop.
Serve with foil around handle.
Makes 6 pops.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Lightly pound chicken breasts between sheets of wax paper to an even thickness.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, oregano, pepper and salt.
Coat each chicken piece with egg, then with crumb mixture pressing crumbs firmly and thoroughly over chicken surface.
Pour enough oil into a large skillet to make 1/4-inch depth.
Heat over medium high heat.
Saute chicken, two pieces at a time, until golden brown, about 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper toweling; keep warm.
Repeat with remaining chicken pieces, adding a little more oil if needed.

title: plucking cake
directions: Melt and heat oleo, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Butter pan real well.
Cut 1 1/2 cans biscuits into quarters.
Layer in tube pan; pour melted ingredients over biscuits and nuts (optional).
Quarter next 1 1/2 cans of biscuits and pour balance of mixture over this.
Bake for 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: ho-bo-casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Put meat back into skillet; add sweet pepper.
Cook until peppers change color.
Add all other ingredients except cheese. Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
(Put in oven or microwave.)
Cook only until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: pink fluff salad
