directions: Soften cream cheese with cherry juice.
Add pineapple and cherries; mix well.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream. Refrigerate until served.

title: hardee's rise and shine biscuits
directions: Bake at 425° until they rise, but don't let them brown unless you are going to eat them as soon as cooked.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Melt margarine in large fry pan. Saute chicken pieces until lightly browned. Remove from pan; add onion to pan drippings. Blend in flour, paprika, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth; cook stirring constantly until thick and smooth. Stir in sour cream and Worcestershire Sauce. Mix 1/2 of sauce with the cooked noodles. Pour into shallow 3 qt. casserole. Arrange chicken pieces on noodles. Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Bake in slow (325°) oven 1 hour until chicken is tender.

title: dot edge's christmas fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers with rolling pin.
Mix all other ingredients with cracker crumbs and fold together well.
Place in pans and refrigerate 2 nights at least.
When hardened, let set out for 2 to 3 hours and it will release from mold.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: Mix in ice cream freezer.
Finish filling with sweet milk. Freeze and set.

title: mock cheese souffle
directions: Using 9 x 13 inch baking pan, lay bread out covering bottom and up onto sides of pan.
Mix all other ingredients together in a bowl and pour over bread.

title: north dakota ranch beans
directions: Mix together and simmer for 2 hours at 250°.
Feeds a crowd!

title: rumaki
directions: Drain water chestnuts and marinate in soy sauce several hours. Cut water chestnuts in half if very large.
Roll in sugar.
Cut bacon slices in half crosswise and again lengthwise.
Wrap water chestnuts in bacon slices.
Secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 425° until bacon is crisp.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 16 to 20.
(May be made day before and refrigerated.
Before serving, reheat 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve in chafing dish.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar or chocolate chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pita bread snack(a favorite vbs bible times snack)
directions: Cut pita bread halves into halves again to make triangles. Spread cream cheese inside pita triangles.
Chop olives and sprinkle them on cream cheese.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Mix muffin mix, egg and milk; set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put sliced apples in pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients together until crumbly.
If ingredients are too moist, add a little flour.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood and rice
directions: Cook vegetables in 1/4 cup water until tender-crisp.
Add rice, shrimp, crab meat, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Mix well. Turn into buttered shallow casserole.
Tip with rice cereal.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: *I use Peter Pan peanut butter.

title: juicy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan with aluminum foil.
Mix cereal, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into milk, then roll in cereal mixture until well coated.
Place chicken, skin side up in pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake until chicken is done, about 1 hour.
Do not turn chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dressing for chicken or turkey
directions: Combine.
Add enough water to make very moist.
Bake at 350° until light brown on top.
Cooked chicken may be added and topped with your favorite chicken gravy or use canned cream of chicken soup and enough water to make as thin as gravy.
Sprinkle with chopped dried parsley.
Bake as directed.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all together until well blended.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Microwave chocolate with 1/4 cup water at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until melted.
Remove and stir until completely melted.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mash salmon, including bones, skin and liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until firm.

title: martha washington creams
directions: Melt paraffin over low heat and stir in chocolate chips. Cream sugar, milk and butter; add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Roll into balls and dip in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until cool.

title: easy chocolate chip fudge
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and chips in glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High (full power) about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until mixture is smooth when stirred.
Add chopped nuts, if desired, and vanilla.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Cover; chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: rice with peas
directions: Fry the ham for 3 to 5 minutes in the oil.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, Sazon and the salt.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add peas and 4 cups of water.
Let it come to a boil.
Add the rice; stir it.
Leave the rice uncovered until all the water is almost absorbed, then cover for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Bake all ingredients at 350° for 45 minutes in round Corning Ware.
Serve with sourdough bread, crackers or whatever.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla. Mix well.

title: sunny's chicken salad
directions: Cut up chicken and two chicken breasts.
Skin chicken and remove as much fat as possible.
Put in large pot and cover with water.
Add celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until done, about 30 minutes.
Debone chicken, cube and combine with chopped celery, onion, mayonnaise and garlic salt. Refrigerate.
Serves 10.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Mix on medium to high 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured round pans, reserving 1 tablespoon batter for filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: toasted onion canapes
directions: Toast one side of bread rounds under broiler on baking sheet. Spread onion, mayonnaise and cheese mixture on untoasted side. Broil 3 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 20.

title: toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix/cream Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add vanilla, water and eggs. Mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. In 350° oven, melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Remove and sprinkle with sugar, nuts, coconut and cherries. Top with pineapple. To reserved juice, add water to measure liquid specified on cake package. Prepare as package directs. Spread over fruit. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until tests done. Cool 5 minutes; invert onto large serving dish.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 round pans or a 9 x 11 x 1/2-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes; remove from mixer.
Stir in boiling water; batter will be thin.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes for rounds, or 35 to 40 minutes for other pan, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake completely before frosting.

title: tiger paws
directions: Melt white chocolate and pour over other ingredients.
Stir until all coated.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: mushroom, celery and pimento salad
directions: Wipe mushrooms clean of any dirt and slice caps and stems thinly into a bowl.
Add celery, pimientos or red peppers and chives or onions.

title: steak skillet supper
directions: In skillet, quickly brown
meat in hot oil.
Add gravy, water and spaghetti sauce, stir.	Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes, stirring
occasionally.
Add
zucchini,
cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes
or until zucchini is to desired tenderness. Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together. Top with marshmallows, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: *One
ounce package butterscotch pieces may be used instead of the chocolate for a light butterscotch flavor.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut stew pieces in half.
Fry, adding sliced onion, salt and pepper.
Add water and remaining spices.
Simmer on medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
When meat is tender, add macaroni.
Cook until done.
Serve.

title: beef patties
directions: Put bread and water in a bowl.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well and shape into six (1/2-inch thick) patties.
Cook in greased frypan over medium heat, turning once to brown both sides.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix butterscotch pudding and 2 cups milk at high speed until well blended.
Stir in whipped topping.
Dipping cookies in milk, line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; put 1/2 pudding mixture over cookies.
Make another layer of cookies, then the rest of pudding mixture.
Crumble some cookies and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Chill.
Serve with a spoon of Cool Whip topping over each serving (optional).
Keeps well in refrigerator 4 to 6 days.

title: french canadian meat pies(makes 2)
directions: Combine pork and beef in large pan.
Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring, until meat is brown.
Then drain.
Stir in poultry seasoning, salt, celery salt, pepper, sage and water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in mashed potatoes.

title: sticks and stones snack
directions: Heat the oven to 300°.
Mix the cereal and pretzel sticks in an ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Stir the margarine and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl.
Pour over the cereal mixture.
Stir until the cereal is evenly coated.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes, stirring several times.
Stir in the raisins.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 8 cups of snack.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup nuts.
Form into a ball. Cover with chopped nuts.

title: powdered sugar glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients well; spread on warm cake.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, then spices. Add soda to applesauce. Mix in flour, then raisins and nuts, etc. Beat after each addition.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Blend in condensed milk slowly.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until foamy. Continue beating, adding sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until egg whites peak.
Fold 6 tablespoons of the meringue into the filling mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake in a slow oven (330°) until golden brown.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat everything but milk at low speed until well mixed.
Add milk slowly until desired consistency.

title: all in one dinner in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Get a piece of foil out big enough to seal all ingredients in.
Place steak on foil; season with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place sliced potatoes on top of steak.
Add drained can of green beans on top.
Sprinkle onion soup on top and then add 4 tablespoons butter on top.
Seal all in foil.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Mix stir-fry sauce, water and sugar in small bowl and set aside.
Put oil into wok and heat over medium-high.
Place chops in wok and brown on both sides.
Remove chops to plate, reserving as much oil as possible.
Stir-fry onion slices in same pan until light gold brown.

title: holiday ham and chili cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, deviled ham, scallions and chilies.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into a ball.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Put butter in medium bowl; beat in lemon juice and egg with fork.
In another bowl, mix bread crumbs, cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken slices into egg mixture; coat evenly with crumb mixture.
In a large frying pan, melt 2 teaspoons of butter. Cook chicken over low heat, turning once, until done.
Serve with spaghetti in a red sauce.

title: perfect mashed potatoes(low-fat)
directions: Slice potatoes in half and scoop out flesh.
Mash potatoes and garlic or onions with fork or potato masher.
Whip in skim milk. Add black pepper and salt.

title: "k" cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Add vanilla, salt and peanut butter.
When peanut butter is melted, add cereal.
Stir until coated.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut when cooled.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 dozen.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Rinse beans.
Add to 2 quarts cold water. Bring to boiling. Simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Cover.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Drain, reserving liquid.
Measure 2 cups liquid, adding water if needed.
Mix with molasses, sugar and mustard. Score half of salt pork. Grind remainder.
In 2-quart casserole, combine beans, ground pork and onion.
Pour sugar mixture over. Top with scored pork. Cover and bake at 300° for 5 to 7 minutes. Add liquid, if needed.
Serves 8.

title: blackberry puddin'
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter together.
Add the flour, baking powder, salt and milk; mix well.
Then pour blackberries on top. Pour 1 cup sugar over and the boiling water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°, until top is golden brown.
Will take about 50 minutes.

title: chestnuts and sugar plums
directions: Combine chestnuts and prunes in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Combine juice, butter, sugar and salt in bowl; mix well.
Pour over prune mixture.
Bake until just heated at 350°.
Stir occasionally. Spoon in serving dishes.
Serve with pork or poultry.
Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.
Cool completely.

title: idiot's delight
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in a double boiler.
Mix noodles and peanuts in melted butterscotch.
Drop on wax paper.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix together; serve on wheat crackers and top with cocktail sauce.
Best if you let sit overnight.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fry loose sausage; do not drain.
Cook chicken.
Cut up. Prepare shrimp.
Set all aside.
Prepare rice as per directions on box.
Add in tomato sauce (do not make it soupy), sausage, chicken and shrimp (also dump in grease from sausage).
Add in red pepper to taste.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to boil.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted. Slowly add gelatine.
Add shrimp, celery and onion; stir.
Remove from heat; cool for 5 minutes.
Add mayonnaise; stir.
Place in greased mold (3 1/2 cup mold) in refrigerator until firm.

title: oven baked pork and beans
directions: You may add any meat ingredient also, cut up ham, crisp bacon, cooked ground beef, etc.

title: baked tomato pie
directions: Layer pepper, tomatoes and onion in pie pan.
Mix basil, grated cheese and mustard.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread over top of pie.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pie crust for unbaked fillings
directions: With pastry blender or fork, blend crust mix with brown sugar. Mix in walnuts.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Combine well and press into a buttered and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool before filling.

title: mexican salsa dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add salsa and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour cheese on top of mixture, let melt. Serve with nacho chips.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit on bottom of 13x9x2 pan. Spread evenly.
Mix soft butter and cake mix.
Place mixture on top of fruit.
Bake for 30-45 mins.
Layer should be golden brown. Can be served with ice cream.
If using a glass dish, temperature is 325°.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Pour in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the wizard's giant pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in
a large mixing bowl. Add sugar and salt.
Stir well. Add flour, one cup at a time, beating after each addition. Turn dough out onto a floured board and knead until smooth.
Cut off small chunks of the dough. Roll into 1/2-inch ropes and twist into pretzel shapes.
Dust cookie sheets with cornmeal.
Arrange pretzels on the sheets.
Brush tops of pretzels with beaten egg and sprinkle generously with salt.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 or 8 large pretzels.

title: baked hamburger casserole
directions: Blend together beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties.
Arrange layer of potatoes in a greased glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Season.
Then add layers of corn and of beans and arrange meat patties on top.
Pour the tomatoes over all and bake in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar and egg yolk.
Stir in flour, salt and vanilla.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with melted Hershey bar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar and oleo until it forms a soft ball (when tested in cold water).
Take off stove and add marshmallows, beat until dissolved.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour in lightly greased pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Add milk to eggs.
Spread rolls on pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
Layer with sausage, hash browns, egg mixture and then cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carratiera sauce - no cook
directions: Blend.
Let stand 1/2 hour or more.
Pour over hot drained pasta.
Great for summertime!

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes. Serve hot with cold milk, tastes great with cinnamon or fried apples.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add all ingredients, adding 5 cans of water.
Stir occasionally so rice doesn't settle.
Cook according to rice directions.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together corn, Jiffy corn bread mix, eggs and sugar.
Fold in 1 cup sour cream.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: May add shredded cheese to top.

title: dan's homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add kidney beans.
Heat until beans are hot.
You can add more tomato juice to make a thinner chili.

title: easy fried pies
directions: Cut butter into flour with pastry blender.
Combine milk and egg yolk.
Pour over flour mixture, stirring to mix well.
Roll out small portions on floured surface.
Place pie filling in center. Fold over and seal edges.
Fry in deep hot fat until golden brown.

title: prize winner lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt thoroughly in saucepan.
Add hot water and cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Remove from stove; add beaten egg yolks.
Return to stove and cook at low heat, stirring constantly for 6 minutes. Take off stove and add lemon juice and butter.
Cool.
Pour into cooled baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue.

title: spanish rice(large-quantity recipe)
directions: Combine tomatoes, water, onions, pepper and salt;
heat to the boiling point.
Add butter	and rice; cover to bring to boiling point again.
Reduce
heat	and
simmer
until rice is tender. Remove from heat
and
add cheese.	Stir until cheese is melted. Will stay warm
and
fluffy
if covered with heavy cloth and then with pot cover.
Yields
servings
of 1 cup each.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix ingredients together until well blended.
Eat and enjoy!!

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all and roll out.
Cut around a saucer.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper and let set.

title: lemon chicken cutlets
directions: Bread and fry chicken.
Place in long baking dish.
In medium size bowl, mix together broth, butter, flour, lemon and seasonings. Pour over cutlets.
Bake at 350° for approximately 3/4 of an hour, covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes.

title: white turkey chili
directions: Simmer turkey, carrots and celery in broth for 10 minutes or until turkey is no longer pink. Drain all but 1 cup of liquid. Add beans, chilies and spices. Simmer 10 minutes. Top with shredded cheese.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season and lightly brown pork chops.
Mix other ingredients. Arrange pork chops in a shallow baking dish; pour sauce over them. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or baked potatoes.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour mixture and pumpkin pie spice.
Using electric mixer on medium speed, mix together brown and granulated sugars.
Beat in butter.
Add egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed, light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Drop by round spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake until slightly browned along edges, about 20 minutes.
Cool cookies on flat surface.

title: cauliflower supreme(low-fat)
directions: Break off flowerets of cauliflower. Slice lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Simmer cauliflower in boiling water in covered pan for 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; drain.
Fold in grapes and almonds. Return to burner until heated through.

title: bread(original from alberta b. seitz)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In large bowl, put sugar, salt and shortening; add hot water.
When dissolved, add milk, then yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
On floured board, roll dough into a large rectangle; fold into thirds, roll again; repeat 4 or 5 times.
Place in greased pan and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400°.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour and oleo and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread onto cooled crust.
Mix pudding mixes and milk until thick.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top.
May garnish with walnuts.
Chill several hours.

title: grilled and chilled japanese eggplant
directions: Prepare a charcoal fire.
Grill the eggplants over hot coals until soft, about 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently.
Remove and set aside until cool enough to handle.
Combine the chicken broth, bonito flakes, soy sauce and rice wine in a saucepan. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the ginger and remove from the heat. Use a sharp knife to slice the eggplant lengthwise into 4 slices, without cutting through the stem end.
Fan each eggplant out on a platter and drizzle with the sauce.
Refrigerate until completely cool, or up to 24 hours, before serving.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and cheese. Blend with crab meat, mayonnaise and garlic salt; spread over halved English muffins. Place waxed paper between muffins and freeze.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into fourths (about 1 1/2 cups).
Saute onion and celery in margarine in Dutch oven (deep pan) until crisp and tender.
Stir soup, bouillon, lemon juice, pepper and nutmeg into sauteed mixture.
Add chicken and spaghetti and stir.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.

title: microwave irish stew
directions: Place beef cubes in 3-quart microproof casserole or baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Stir together gravy mix and water. Pour over meat.
Cook, covered, on 70 (Roast) for 50 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Add vegetables and mix to cover with gravy.
Cook, covered, on 50 (Simmer) for 40 to 50 minutes or until vegetables and meat are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir Bisquick and sugar together.
Add slightly beaten eggs and remaining ingredients until well mixed.
(Do not use mixer.) Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until well done; drain and set aside to cool (for cutting).
In medium bowl, mix soup, sour cream, green chilies and seasonings.
Cut chicken into small pieces and stir into soup mixture.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass casserole dish.
Lay tortilla flat on hard surface; place 2 to 3 tablespoons of chicken mixture across center of tortilla. Sprinkle with 1 to 2 tablespoons of cheese (reserve 1/2 cup cheese for topping).

title: frankfurter tuckaway
directions: Cook 4 ounces of macaroni.
Cut 4 frankfurters lengthwise and insert slice of cheese.
Wrap with a slice of bacon.
Fasten with a toothpick.
Mix soup with milk.
Bring to a boil and add macaroni.
Put in greased baking dish and top with frankfurters. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Separate eggs beating yolk until thick.
Add yolks and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Alternate flour and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 365° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Buy thick pork chops, butcher will slit a pocket for you.
Mix stuffing (ingredients above).
Fill pockets of chops and place remainder around chops in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (until tender).
You can use Stove Top dressing.

title: natchez sugar pralines
directions: Boil first six ingredients until mixture forms ball in ice water, then add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add pecans and spoon out onto waxed paper or buttered plate.

title: shrimp dip(yield:  3 cups)
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl.
In a mixer, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except chips).
Chill to blend flavors.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with chips.

title: beef gravy and biscuits
directions: Mix flour and milk; add to margarine and beef, cut in little pieces.
Cook in a pot until thickened.
Add more milk if needed. Stir constantly.
Pour over biscuits.

title: billy's venison soup
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for two hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake crust.
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Add strawberries. Pour into pie crust.
Chill overnight.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies in food processor or blender, crush until mixture looks like dirt.
It helps if cookies are frozen.
Set aside.

title: fresh veggie appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 rectangles.
Press onto bottom and up sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan to form crust.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing, sour cream, dill and onion salt until well blended.
Spread on crust.
Top with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
makes 24.

title: quick vegetable beef soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven or kettle, cook beef and onion until beef and onion are tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in beef broth, mixed vegetables, undrained tomatoes, potato, celery, marjoram, oregano, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Discard bay leaf.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: tumbleweed's queso
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add jalapenos and chilies. Add all other ingredients, cheese last.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix water, white vinegar, salt and sugar well and pour over pickles and other ingredients cold.
Let set out several days before putting in refrigerator.
Place cucumbers in bottom of a glass gallon jar, then alternate with fresh dill, onions, garlic and jalapeno peppers.
(I use hot crushed peppers if I don't have the jalapeno peppers; don't use too many peppers as it will make the pickles too hot.)

title: mustard pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in quart jar.
Do not overpack in jars.
Put mustard, salt and sugar on top.
Pour vinegar over them.
Shake 3 or 4 mornings before putting them away.

title: yule log
directions: (Can use 1/2 pound cherries and pineapple as an option instead of the mixed fruit.)

title: trifle
directions: Prepare in a trifle bowl, a large brandy sniffer or a large flat glass bowl.
Prepare devil's food cake in a 9 x 13-inch square pan.
Place 1/2 of cake in bowl (after baking).
Spread 1 can of chocolate pudding over cake.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of candy mixture (brickle and chocolate).
Cover with 1/2 (6 ounces) of Cool Whip. Repeat all steps.
Save some candy to sprinkle on top for decoration.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Can be frozen!

title: bolognese veal braised in milk
directions: Rub veal with oil and butter and place in roasting pan along with a few sprigs of rosemary and sage leaves.
Put pan in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn frequently and baste from time to time with the meat juices.
Remove veal from pan and place in covered casserole.
Add enough milk to immerse 2/3 of veal.
Cover casserole, leaving top ajar.
Cook slowly approximately 2 hours or until meat is done.
Turn and baste meat occasionally, adding any remaining milk.
When meat is cooked, remove to a platter and keep warm.
Milk in casserole should have coagulated into small nut brown clusters.
If not, raise heat to high.
Cook, uncovered, briskly until milk further reduces and darkens.
Skim off fat and discard, being careful not to remove any coagulated milk clusters.
Add warm water, turn heat to high, boil away all water while scraping and loosening all cooking residue in casserole.
Taste and correct seasonings.
Carve into 3/8-inch thick slices.
Spoon sauce over meat and serve immediately.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine the raisins, water and soda and let stand for 2 hours. Add both sugars, salt, flour (one cup at a time) and nuts. Grease and flour two (1 pound) coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix meat, soups, part of grated cheese and the cooked macaroni.
Pour half of the mixture in a lasagna dish or other baking dish.
Break 1/2 can of dried onions over.
Cover with rest of mixture.
Save a handful of grated cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Just before removing from oven, add the rest of dried onions and bake 5 more minutes and serve.
Enjoy!

title: white wonder cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Blend until smooth after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Stir well.
Add pineapple, ice cream and nuts.
Mix together well.
Chill before serving.

title: 9 layer guacamole dip
directions: Layer ingredients in this order on dinner plate and serve with tortilla chips.

title: missouri no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan.
Cook at full rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan; cover with 3 strips bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour over meat loaf one 8 ounce can Hunt's tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over low heat; add soups and mushrooms.
Stir; remove from heat.
Add pimento, chicken, spaghetti and sour cream.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased tube or Bundt pan at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
These cakes freeze well or will keep several days at room temperature, staying moist.

title: strawberry gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold liquid.
Blend in sour cream until smooth.
Pour into mold.
Add drained fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate.

title: molasses crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar with hands.
Save 1 cup for topping.
In remainder of crumbs, add molasses, cold water and baking soda.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour into greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If glass dish is used, bake at 325°.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Place in double boiler and mix well until all ingredients form large ball.
Add nuts.
You may need a little more milk.
Press into 6 x 6-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger; season to taste.
Layer Tater Tots in 2
1/2 quart casserole with hamburger.
Combine mushroom soup, milk and dry onion soup.
Pour over ingredients.
Stir slightly to
allow liquids
to
drain	down.
Top with onion rings. Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix with hands in a big boll hamburger meat, 1 egg, 3 shakes of garlick powder, 3 shake of pepper and 3 shakes of salt and 3 shakes of ongion powder.
Crombell tost in to small pices; make in to small balls and cook in scilet till well done.

title: french vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Reduce heat and stir in soup and 6 cans water.
Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and basil.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Reheat to boiling.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until vegetables and meat are tender.
Stir in cheese.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well.
Place in covered bowl.
Put 1 cup sugar over top. Let stand at least 1 day.
This will last a long time in refrigerator.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, shortening, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Take out 1/2 cup for on top of cake.
Add cooked raisins to this mixture, then add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls soda to 2 cups buttermilk or sour milk; add to first mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese. Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth.
Combine both mixtures and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in 8-inch plastic flowerpot . Start with Oreos and end with Oreos.
Garnish with gummie worms and silk flowers.
Add a garden spade to serve.

title: indiana chili
directions: Saute ground beef until done.
Add kidney beans and tomato juice.
Add chili powder and sugar.
Meanwhile, saute onion slices in butter or margarine.
When onions are cooked (clear), add both onions and butter to meat mixture.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Serve with oyster crackers.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Separate dinner rolls; spread with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Roll sausage link, starting from wide end. Cut each roll into 3 or 4 pieces.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dannon apple spice cake
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients except raisins; blend well using spoon. Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean, 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Loosen cake from sides with spatula.
Invert on plate.
Cool completely.

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Slice potatoes and cut into strips.
Spray jelly roll pan with vegetable spray, cover with potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Remove from oven, sprinkle on cheeses and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: chicken and shrimp creole
directions: Cut any visible fat from chicken; remove skin and cut into cubes.
In large pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Cook chicken for about 3 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Add onions and garlic; cook for about 3 minutes, until softened.
Stir in peppers.
Add tomatoes, breaking up with back of spoon.
Add stock, thyme, oregano and cayenne; bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes, or until most of the liquid is absorbed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with all ingredients. Cover and chill.
This is a good change from the usual green salad and complements most any meal.
Serves 6.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla into blender container.
Cover and process at mix until sugar is dissolved and eggs lemon colored.
Remove feeder cap and add milk.
Continue to process until blended.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for about 30 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: cocktail wraps
directions: Separate dough along perforations into 8 triangles; cut each lengthwise into thirds.
Wrap dough around Hillshire Farm little smokies or wieners.
Press ends together to seal.
Bake as directed on dough package.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar together until light; add milk, then melted butter and extract.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder twice and add the liquid mixture to them; beat well.
Bake about 45 minutes in moderate 350° oven.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in saucepan until done; drain, then let cool. Mix together, in separate bowl, mayonnaise, mustard, milk, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Add remaining ingredients to potatoes and toss, mixing in mayonnaise mixture.
Serve cold.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put potatoes in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes on High.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully, do not rip potato skin.
Scoop out potato pulp, leaving 1/4 inch of potato around skin.
Brush generously with soy sauce (optional, but will enhance flavor).
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serve with sour cream if desired.
Serves 2.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 15 minutes.
Cook bacon until crisp in frying pan.
Saute onions in bacon drippings.
Add brown sugar, pepper, carrots and bacon.
Cook until heated.

title: miniature reubens
directions: Cover bread with dressing, sauerkraut, corned beef and cheese. Bake at 400° until cheese melted, about 10 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cover again with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add other ingredients (tie spice in bag). Cook 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 30 (2-inch) foil cupcake liners in small muffin pans or on cookie sheet.
Combine brownie mix, fudge packet from mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Place 2 level tablespoons batter in each foil cupcake liner.
Bake in each foil cupcake liner.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Push 1 peanut butter cup candy in center of each cupcake until even with surface of brownie.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Cool completely.

title: bread deluxe
directions: Combine yeast, 1 cup of warm water and sugar; let stand 10 minutes.
Add to beaten eggs, salt, oil, 1 cup sugar and 5 cups of warm water.
Add yeast mixture, then gradually add 15 cups of flour to which you have added 1 cup of powdered milk. Mix until smooth.
Let rise.
Knead down.
Put into loaf pans; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 loaves.

title: breakfast balls
directions: Cook 1 pound of the sausage to a crumble and drain off the fat.
Chop the ham.
Mix all the sausage well with the ham and other ingredients, with salt and pepper to taste.
Form into large balls to make a muffin shape and place them in a large muffin pan. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes, turn up the heat and bake 15 minutes more to brown.
Serve with hot currant sauce or jelly.
Good with scrambled or baked eggs.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda; stir in caraway seed.
Cut in oleo; add raisins.
Combine buttermilk and egg; blend in flour mixture.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead until smooth about 25 times.
Shape into a smooth ball; place into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Cut a 4-inch cross about 1/4-inch across top.
Lightly beat egg yolk and water; brush over loaf and bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften, add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup, salt and eggs.
Stir in pecans, pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel apples and oranges and
cut
fine. Mix all ingredients together and add 3 or 4 tablespoons mayonnaise.

title: orange tofu(great for toddlers)
directions: Saute tofu cubes in oil or butter for 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add tamari and ginger and continue cooking over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add orange juice and cook for 1 more minute.
Serve over Texmati brown rice.

title: red velvet cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, soda and cocoa. Add alternately flour, butter and buttermilk. Pour into 2 well greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Scald milk.
Add a little milk to egg mixture at a time.
Stir constantly over medium heat, about 15 minutes, until coats the spoon.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream and dash of nutmeg.

title: baked fish
directions: Take haddock pieces the size of your hand and place in glass dish with just enough melted butter to cover the bottom of dish. Take finely crushed bread crumbs (seasoned or plain) and sprinkle over top.
Add melted Cheez Whiz and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Run berries and apples through food chopper.
Also add orange (pulp and peel).
Add sugar; mix.
Let stand several hours to blend.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and cool under cold water.
Separate spaghetti and start mixing vegetables between layers of spaghetti. Use whole bottle of Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.
Make day before.
Keep stirring so flavors will mix.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water and salt about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Meanwhile, saute the onion in butter until tender.
When potatoes are cooked, stir in onion, corn, pimiento, milk, half and half, brown sugar, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer until soup is slightly thickened.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute beef, salt, and onion in skillet.
Drain and let cool. In a large bowl place lettuce, beef, grated cheese, corn chips, and dressing and mix thoroughly.
Serve immediately.

title: creamy chocolate nog
directions: In blender container beat egg until light in color.
Add ice cream, milk and Nestle Quik.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.
Makes three 6-ounce servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage coarsely; steam lightly until just wilted in water with a pinch of salt and sugar.
Melt butter in a large (13 x 9-inch) Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of Frosted Flakes over butter.
In a saucepan, mix celery soup, milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg.
Spread cabbage over crumbs in Pyrex dish.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Top with grated cheese and other 1 cup of Frosted Flakes crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch. Sprinkle turkey, onions, cheese, mushrooms and salt in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 7 servings; 145 calories per serving.

title: pizza on a bun
directions: *You can use one of the three meats or all.

title: candied nuts(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Mix sugar, cream, water and vanilla. Cook to soft ball stage. Add nuts and stir until nuts are coated. Pour onto wax paper. Separate with 2 forks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables, poultry seasoning and garlic salt in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir baking mix and milk until blended.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 30 to 32 minutes or until crust is light golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in pan and boil 2 minutes.
Let cool and add peanut butter, vanilla, nuts and rolled oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: shredded hashed brown potatoes
directions: Peel and shred the potatoes (should be 3 cups).
Rinse the potatoes and drain well (pat with paper towels to make as dry as possible).

title: oyster dressing
directions: Dice up potatoes, celery and onions.
Cover with water; add salt, pepper and a chunk of butter.
Cook until very done.
Break bread into chunks and using 1 stick margarine and 1 loaf bread at a time, toast them in a large pan on the stove until brown.
Stir while toasting.
Mash the potato mixture fine in the juice they were cooked in.
Pour over bread.
Pour juice from giblets over bread; add chopped giblets.
Beat eggs; add half and half.
Pour over bread.
Chop oysters and add to dressing; add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir all together.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Sift flour 3 times with soda.
Add 1/2 cup at a time to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pat into burgers. Grill, pan-fry or bake until done. Garnish as you wish.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut oleo into dry cake mix; add nuts and spread over filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Most prefer butter brickle on apple, while many enjoy the white mix on cherry.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Dissolve candy in water and jello.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In 1 quart scalded milk, put oil and sugar. Let cool to lukewarm. In pint of warm milk, put yeast; let dissolve without stirring. When first mixture is cool, add yeast and milk to it. Add enough flour to make soft dough; cover and let rise at room temperature until it doubles in bulk (about 2 hours). Knead, roll, cut, stretch, dip in melted butter. Fold over and butter tops. Let rise for 2 hours again; bake at 450° until brown. Makes about 100.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: In saucepan, blend sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir into eggs.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Chill.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: carrot pineapple salad
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Mash and sprinkle with sugar; set aside. Dissolve Jell-Os in boiling water, then add cold water, carrots and pineapple.
Stir well.
Congeal.
Top with a dab of mayonnaise.

title: granola
directions: Mix and spread 1/2-inch deep on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool, crumble and add nuts, seeds, raisins or other dried fruit.

title: cherry squares
directions: Put melted butter in a bowl; add sugar and mix well; add egg and blend well. Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Then add nuts and cherries. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with Almond-Cherry Flavored Frosting.

title: classic coke cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour and sugar.
Combine melted butter, cocoa and Coke. Add to flour and sugar mixture, stirring well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Fold in the miniature marshmallows. Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and frost while still warm.

title: strawberry chiffon
directions: In a small saucepan melt butter; stir in crumbs.
Pat firmly on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Chill.
In large bowl dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and strawberries.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared vanilla wafers pan.
Chill for 2 hours or more. Garnish with Cool Whip or strawberries.

title: kaiser macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients together; cover and let stand overnight. Recipe may be doubled for larger groups.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine. Cook until clear and thick. Mix with 4 cups rhubarb, cut up, and top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: salsa in a shell
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and salsa until well blended. Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Cut top off bread and save.
Hollow out bread.
Spoon cheese mixture into bread and cover with bread top. Wrap in foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: humble pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium-size bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar,
butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Then add
flour,
baking powder and soda.
Lastly, add crushed bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix together with garlic salt and Tabasco sauce.
Let chill.
On wax paper, roll mixture into logs or ball.
Roll in chili powder and pecans.
Chill until served.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in stockpot and saute onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Stir in vegetables and seasonings, broth and drained beans.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes.
Add tomato, pasta, and tomato sauce and simmer until pasta is done.
Add cabbage (optional), salt, and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until cabbage wilts.
Serve in bowls with parmesan cheese sprinkled on top of soup.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, pumpkin, sugar, baking soda and eggs with electric mixer until well blended.
Line greased jelly roll pan with wax paper and pour batter in this.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Flip cake on dish towel that has been covered in confectioners sugar.
Let cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to oil and sugar mixture, blending well.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Cut each wing in 3 parts.
Discard tips.
Place chicken wings in shallow glass dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Cook in oven for 1 hour, turning after first half hour.
Makes about 30 appetizers.
Oven temperature is 375°.

title: "grate" zucchini bread(low-fat)
directions: In large bowl, combine the whole wheat and white flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
In a medium bowl,
mix together the egg white, whole egg, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add this mixture to the flour mixture, stirring the ingredients to combine them well.
Stir in the nuts and/or raisins, if desired.
Pour the batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake the bread in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until
a pick inserted in the center of the bread comes out clean.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good and easy.

title: pineapple layer cake frosting
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding until well blended. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Makes enough to frost three 9-inch layers. Preparation time: 0:15.

title: chocolate scrump pie(named by tim fowler)
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Take 3/4 of whipped cream and mix with all the pudding.
Add coconut, pecans and chocolate chips to the mixture.
Fold mixture into pie crust.
Take remaining Cool Whip and spread on top of pie.
Now, take remaining coconut, pecans and chocolate chips and sprinkle them over the pie.
Place in the refrigerator for about 2 hours and it's ready to eat.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix for filling.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining dry cake mix, margarine and egg.
Mix until thoroughly combined. Press evenly into bottom and sides of prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Meanwhile, combine reserved cake mix, brown sugar, syrup, vanilla and 3 eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour filling over baked crust.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Return to oven and bake for 30 to 35 minutes until filling is set. Cool and cut into 36 bars.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, drain fat and set aside.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter or margarine.
Stir in soups and rice; mix well. Fold in sausage.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish, sprinkle with crumbled cornflakes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish; set aside.
Pare, quarter, core and thinly slice apples.
You should have 6 cups.
In large mixing bowl, place apples, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice; toss lightly to mix.
Place in prepared baking dish; set aside.

title: taco soup
directions: Add all ingredients in large kettle, stir to mix taco seasoning. Bring to a boil, boil 15 minutes. Serve with toppings: grated cheese, corn chips, sour cream, salsa, chilies, or black olives.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs, then flour, milk, vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Prebake pie shells 5 minutes.
After prebaking 5 minutes, pour mixture in shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Press softened cream cheese in bottom of small Pyrex dish. Spread chili on top of cream cheese; sprinkle onions on top of chili.
Then sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over peaches, then the chopped nuts and coconut. Dribble melted oleo over top and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix well and serve with chips.

title: sweet sue chicken casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in oil over low heat until tender.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Layer in the following order: half of the chicken and dumplings, cheese, spaghetti, vegetables, half of the chicken and dumplings and soup.
Cook in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until brown around the edges.

title: no weep meringue
directions: In a small saucepan, combine cornstarch, sugar and water. Heat until clear over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar a small amount at a time.
Add cornstarch mixture and beat until peaks form.
Put on your favorite pie and bake until brown.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Drain peaches in bowl and chill.
Mix pudding with milk and refrigerate 5 minutes.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold in chilled pudding mixture.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Add sherry if you wish, mixing well.
Spread over peaches.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: plain muffins
directions: Combine milk, egg and shortening.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix with liquid mixture, blending together with 25 to 30 strokes.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° 15 minutes for small muffins or 30 minutes for large muffins.
Yields 12 large or 20 small muffins.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Hook tips of wings over opposite end of bones to form triangle.
Fry slightly in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove lid, increase heat and cook until liquid is almost gone.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Boil prawns/shrimp until they turn pink, approximately 5 to 8 minutes or saute prawns in olive oil.
Cook vermicelli/pasta according to package directions.
Wait until all other ingredients are ready.
(Serve hot.)

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shells and sprinkle with the pecans.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake for 25 minutes longer.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate pudding bake
directions: Sift 3/4 cup sugar and flour with 2 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt into a 9-inch square pan.
Stir in milk, oleo and vanilla; spread evenly in pan.
Combine next 3 ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake pudding at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: ham and mushrooms
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart cooking bowl, cook onion and butter on High for 2 minutes or until slightly softened.
Add mushrooms and cook on High, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once, only until mushrooms are tender, but not shriveled.
Stir in flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt, mixing with fork until it is all absorbed.
Add half and half, stirring to mix well.
Cook on High, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes, until boiling and thickened.
Stir in beef granules, mustard, frozen peas, ham and sherry.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, if needed.
Heat on 30% power, Defrost or Medium-low, about 15 minutes, stirring once.

title: peach crisp
directions: Drain peaches; place in lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with spices.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and melted butter; crumble over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Good served hot or cold.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cut off crust from bread and cube. Melt butter. Add sugar, milk and eggs. Whip together. Add pineapple and bread cubes. Stir together until well mixed. Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° about 1/2 hour or until set.

title: french pancakes
directions: Mix and fry. Butter and sprinkle with powdered sugar and roll pancake.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Stir milk and flour together.
Cook and stir over low heat until sauce simmers and thickens.
Stir in sherry and seasonings. Stir in seafood until heated through.
Top with buttered bread crumbs
and bake until the crumbs are brown on top (400°).

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Form into balls. Put on a baking sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken parisian
directions: Place 4 chicken breasts in pan.
Mix mushroom soup, wine and mushrooms together.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove chicken.

title: crispy coconut shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Combine flour, salt and 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard in a small bowl.
In another small bowl, beat egg and cream.
Combine coconut and bread crumbs on a sheet of wax paper.
Dip shrimp in flour mixture, then in egg/cream mixture, and finally in flour/crumb mixture, coating well.
Refrigerate in a single layer until ready to cook.
Pour oil into medium saucepan to 2-inch depth.
Heat to 350 degrees on deep-fat thermometer.
Fry shrimp, a few at a time in hot oil for about 2 minutes, turning once until golden brown.
Use slotted spoon and remove to paper toweling to drain.
Keep warm in slow oven (200 degrees) until all is done.
Serve with Chinese Mustard Sauce and bottled duck sauce.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter thoroughly; add vanilla. Gradually stir flour into creamed ingredients.
Work nuts in dough.
Chill well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar immediately.
Cool on rack.
Roll in sugar again.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 5 dozen snow balls.

title: recipe for a good church softball game
directions: Preheat the day at a refreshing 75°.
Gently stir one team of softball players and umpires together and carefully pour onto playing field.
Take second team and strategically place off to the side of the field.
Take the strong voiced scorekeepers and place them at 2 different sides.
This method is used to avoid confusion among the players.

title: tabasco pickles
directions: Drain pickles, add sugar and Tabasco sauce. Do not refrigerate for 7 days. Stir every day. On day 8, refrigerate and enjoy.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix graham crackers, melted oleo and sugar.
Press down in bottom of pan.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together; put on top of cracker crumbs, and top cream cheese mixture with pie filling.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; drain.
Mix egg, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Set to one side.
Mix flour, instant potatoes, lemon pepper, salt and pepper.
Marinate mushrooms a few at a time, about 3 to 5 minutes in egg and milk mixture.
Press into flour and potato mixture making sure the mushrooms are coated.
Fry about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done, then take off the bone.
Cut into small pieces.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until done.
Mix in chicken soup, mushroom soup, sour cream and chicken.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers in butter to make a small crust.
Pour in the mixed ingredients, then make a small crust on top.
Bake at 350° or 400° until brown on top, about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix dressing, juice and seasoning mix.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan.
Brush with 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Broil 5 to 7 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes. Turn; brush with remaining dressing mixture.
Continue broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Serve with twisted breadsticks and black beans with chopped red pepper, if desired.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 3
ingredients
together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Mix
remaining
ingredients.
Cook on stove until warm, then pour over
meat.
Cover	meat
with foil.
Does not need water.	Will cook in its own juices.
After baking, drain fat off.
Pour vinegar
mixture
over meat and put back into oven uncovered. Bake until looks glazy.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Saute leeks in butter 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and cook 2 minutes.
Gradually blend in water.
Add salt, pepper and potatoes; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes, partially covered.
Add milk; bring to a simmer.
Blend in cream. Turn off heat and add butter.
Garnish with chives or parsley.

title: corn medley
directions: Combine corn, celery, bouillon cube, and water; simmer until cube is dissolved and vegetables are tender.
Add mushrooms, tomato, salt and pepper.
Simmer briefly.
Serves 6. Fifty calories a serving.

title: baked green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned coconut custard pie
directions: Flute the edges of the pastry; place pastry-lined pie pan in refrigerator to chill.
Heat the milk over very low heat until tiny bubbles appear around the edges of the milk.
Set aside to cool until almost lukewarm.
Beat the eggs in a bowl until whites and yolks are well blended.
(The reserved white is for later use.)
Mix the sugar, salt and cinnamon; stir into the beaten eggs and beat until some of the sugar dissolves.
Add the vanilla and almond extracts to the cooled milk. Gradually pour this mixture into the egg-sugar mixture stirring constantly.
Strain the mixture into a clean bowl.
Stir in the coconut.
Set aside.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix together, place into greased pan, press into bottom of pan. Bake 375 for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa together.
Add buttermilk, Wesson oil, vinegar, vanilla, eggs and food coloring in order and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 3 layer pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add cocoa, butter, vanilla and salt. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cherry salad
directions: To cherry jello add 2 cups hot water, 3/4 cup cold water, crushed pineapple and juice.
To strawberry jello add 2 cups hot water, 3/4 cup cold water and strawberries.
Allow cherry jello to set.
Spread sour cream over cherry jello and pour on partially set strawberry jello layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: In double
boiler,
melt
chips,
milk,
oleo and salt. Remove from
heat	and
add walnuts and vanilla.
Sift and set aside flour,
salt
and
soda.
In
large bowl, blend oleo and brown sugar.
Mix
well and add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well; add flour mix
and
oatmeal.	Press 2/3 of mix in greased 10 x 15-inch
pan. Spread chocolate filling over.
Crumble remaining 1/3
crumb
mix over
filling.
Sprinkle
nuts over this. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Add water and let cook slowly.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Layer potatoes, hamburger, onions, peppers and tomatoes in 2-quart casserole dish.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Garnish with sliced peppers.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: california summer salad
directions: Place all ingredients in an airtight glass jar that can be shaken before each serving.
Allow several hours or overnight for the flavors to blend.
This mixture does not have to be refrigerated.
It can be left out at room temperature, and more ingredients added as needed.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Combine sour cream and honey; set aside.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; saute onion and celery until tender.
In large mixing bowl, combine rice, celery and onion with remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed. Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and onions. Set this mixture aside. Brown hamburger meat; drain. Add tomato sauce and seasonings, then simmer for 10 minutes. Layer meat mixture and noodle mixture in a casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese. Serves 10 to 12.

title: pound cake (almond)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat for about 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: homemade dog treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, cornmeal, liver and garlic together. Add eggs, shell and all.
Mix well so shells are crushed.
If too thick, add water as needed.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and milk.
Circle approximately 10 minutes.
Add salt and butter and circle 3 to 5 minutes.

title: vietnamese fried rice
directions: Wash the
rice.
Cook rice in 3 cups water.
Chop onion and cook
in frypan containing 1 tablespoon oil.
Place small pieces of	pork in oil.
After seasoning with salt, pepper and sugar, fry for
minutes.	Remove	pork and cook shrimp in same manner for only 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp from pan.
Cook peas.
Use another skillet to fry the cooked rice in 1 tablespoon of
oil. Add
pork,	shrimp	and peas to fried rice and cook on
medium heat
for 10 minutes.
You may add a pinch of Accent, if
desired. Yellow food coloring may be added at the time rice is being cooked to add a more appetizing color.

title: calico beans(serves 8)
directions: Cut up bacon and fry until crisp.
Drain on paper towels. Save fat.
Cook beef in bacon fat until browned.
Add onion and sauce until tender.
Drain fat from skillet.
Combine beef, onion, salt, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar in 3-quart baking dish. Partially drain all cans of beans; add to dish, stirring gently until mixed.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and water.
Combine sugar, flour, rolled oats, butter and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cook in oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place layer of broccoli in large, flat casserole, then layer of cheese and layer of Ritz crackers and drizzle with butter. Repeat with second layer.
Heat until hot just before serving. May be made ahead.

title: sticky rolls
directions: Halve biscuits; roll in margarine.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: To make pie shell, beat egg whites with cream of tartar and eggs until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition until stiff.
Add pecans.
Place in a lightly greased 9-inch pie pan, spreading like a pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: corn cakes
directions: Mix well and cook on hot griddle.
Batter will be thin.
Serve for breakfast with syrup or with lunch or dinner for bread substitute.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Place ingredients in large jar.
Refrigerate.
Marinate the mushrooms in the dressing for up to 2 days.
Serves 20.

title: grandma vi's spanish yellow rice
directions: In 1/4 cup vegetable oil, simmer shrimp, onion and green pepper for 3 minutes.
Add tomato juice, saffron, sugar and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add water, salt, pepper and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally until rice is cooked.
Serves 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Stir with fork until blended.
Fry in hot oil until browned.

title: meat balls with mushroom gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup. Form into balls about 1-inch in size. Bake in baking dish in 350° oven for about 1 hour. Drain and return to baking dish. Add mushroom soup. Bake about 15 minutes longer.

title: cornbread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt. In small mixing bowl, beat egg whites and oil. Stir into dry ingredients just until mixed. Spray a 9 x 9 x 2 baking pan with nonstick spray coating. Pour batter into pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Makes 12 servings.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Cook potatoes (peeled and cut into 1/4-inch slices) about 30 minutes in salt water.
Combine soup and milk.
Layer half of potatoes, onion and cheese in a greased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour half of soup mixture over cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: date rolls
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients and boil 8 to 10 minutes in double boiler until thickened.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and nut meats.
Take little pieces and roll in hand, about 2 inches long, in confectioners sugar or coconut.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: strawberry pie filling salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze overnight in a Jell-O mold.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water; let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Add buttermilk and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients. Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture gradually, gently combining with a fork.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large casserole dish, make alternating layers of onions, potatoes and chicken.
Mix together soup and oleo and spread over evenly.
Bake 1 hour.

title: easy ice cream (no eggs)
directions: Mix sugar and pudding mix; add milk (both kinds) and then vanilla.
Freeze in hand or electric freezer.
Fresh fruits may be used by leaving out part of the milk and adding that amount of fruit.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: grant's fruitcake
directions: Cut fruit into small pieces and mix with flour.

title: sour cream torte
directions: Add pudding to cake mix.
Mix and put in 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake as directed on the box.
When cake is cold, cut both layers in half so that you end up with 4 layers.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal bars
directions: Combine all dry ingredients separate.
Beat butter until fluffy.
Add egg, peanut butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in 1/2 cup of the sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Melt butter and add remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Heat until sugar melts and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then remove to cake plate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Mix soups, water and broth.
Heat.
Layer:
bread crumbs, chicken in small pieces, then soup.
Keep layering and make bread crumbs last layer.
Bake 15 minutes at 450° then 30 minutes on 350°

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes in their skin with water in a large pot.
Cook on medium heat until tender.
Drain water and let potatoes cool. Peel potatoes and chop into bite-size pieces.
In large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, onion, sweet pickles, pickle juice, mustard and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle salt onto mixture and stir. Spoon into serving dish and dust lightly with paprika.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice with pudding mix in medium saucepan. Cook until starts to boil, then remove from heat. Allow to cool until clear. Place apples, pineapple and grapes in large bowl. Add pudding mixture and stir gently. Add bananas shortly before serving; stir gently. Decorate top with cherries.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine all dry ingredients, except nuts.
In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Add nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 370° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, 2 cups flour, powdered sugar and pecans, as pie dough.
Pat in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and eggs and blend. Add grated raw apples and sugar. Sift dry ingredients and add to apple mixture. Mix well. Add nuts, raisins, dates and coconut. Bake in a tube cake pan in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: baked sauerkraut and sausage
directions: Wash sauerkraut.
Slice sausage and chop the onion.
Layer sausage, then onions, sauerkraut and brown sugar.
Repeat until all is used.

title: oriental peas
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in skillet and saute.
Add the peas.
Cook for 5 minutes in 1 cup of boiling water and drain. Add pimento, soup, water chestnuts and 1/4 cup liquid from chestnuts.
Mix up.
Put in covered dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: country potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes; place in a pot of cold water.
Cover and boil for approximately 20 minutes, or until soft.
(Or, the potatoes can be microwaved in 1/4-inch water for 10 minutes until soft.) Halfway through the cooking, add the carrot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine eggs, sugar, shortening and applesauce; stir well.
Sift dry ingredients; add a little at a time to the mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: best ever lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, water, beaten egg yolks, lemon juice and margarine together.
Cook in a double boiler until thick (about 25 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add lemon extract and vinegar.
Stir thoroughly and then cool.
Pour into crust.
Cover with meringue and brown.
Serves 6.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can also be microwaved or put in crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: apricot-raisin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover apricots with boiling water and soak about 1/2 hour.
Squeeze juice from orange and add enough boiling water to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Save orange peel.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa and milk together.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes. Take off stove.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir about 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour on buttered plate.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (be sure to drain fruit).
Blend in a small carton of sour cream.
Put in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together all other ingredients; pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: walnut dreams
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter or margarine, salt, walnuts, sherry flavoring and dash of paprika.
Make square sandwiches (cut crust from slices of bread; cut each slice into 4 squares). Spread with cream cheese mixture.
Garnish with stuffed olive slices.

title: janet's quiche
directions: Divide ingredients in half.
Cook spinach; drain well.
Cut ham into chunks.
Place Swiss cheese in bottoms of pie crusts, then spinach, mushrooms and ham.
Beat eggs, half and half, salt, pepper and flour together.
Pour on top of pies.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over pies.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Yields 2 pies.
Enjoy one now and freeze one for later.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans and cover in a large pot with 6 to 8 cups of hot water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour off of heat.
Add another 2 quarts of cold water and ham bone.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes, until beans are tender.
Remove ham bone and trim off meat.
Return to soup.
Makes 3 quarts.
I serve over rice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart, oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.

title: vegetarian chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
