Mix shortening, sugars, yogurt and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
(For a softer, more rounded cookie, add 1/4 cup more flour.)
Stir dry ingredients together; blend in.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned. (Cookies should still be soft.)
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add 3 cups flour and stir. Add remaining
1 1/2 cups flour and stir. Add bag of chocolate chips. Stir. Shape into teaspoon size balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: apple roll
directions: Roll out
dough.
Spread
with	butter,
cinnamon and 4 tablespoons brown
sugar.
Add
cups finely chopped apples; make a roll, then slice about 1/2 inch thick, put in cake pan. Mix 1 cup water and 1 cup molasses; pour over the rolls.
Bake in moderate oven.
Serve with milk.
Eat while hot.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Small measures for 1 cake, large for 2 cake pans.

title: chocolate almond pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and chocolate in milk in double boiler. Remove from heat; cool. Whip the cream until stiff. Fold into chocolate mixture. Add vanilla. Pour into crust and chill. Can be topped with whipped cream, if desired.

title: kentucky corn
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole.
Beat eggs into mixture one at a time.
Add milk or cream.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stir-fried broccoli and beef
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Set aside.
Mix cornstarch with remaining 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in uncovered wok at 300°.
Add broccoli stalk slices, cover; cook 2 minutes.
Add flowerets; cover, cook 2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove broccoli to hot platter. Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil to wok; heat at 375°.
Add meat; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add soy sauce mixture; stir-fry 2 minutes. Return broccoli to wok; mix.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Serve immediately.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Cool. Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar gradually, beating after each addition of ingredients.
Add cooled cornstarch mixture and continue beating until peaks form.
Use as desired.

title: sheila's chicken
directions: Heat oil in frying pan over medium heat. Scramble egg in bowl. Dip chicken in egg and then bread crumbs.
Fry lightly. Take out and pat off excess oil and set aside.
In the same pan, melt butter, slice mushrooms and stir-fry.
Add parsley, chicken broth and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooking wine.
Lay chicken in greased baking pan. Pour mushroom mixture over chicken and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: super spuds
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in lightly salted boiling water about 20 minutes or just until tender.
Cool to room temperature.
Cut potatoes in half.
Using a small spoon or melonballer, remove a small scoop of potato from each potato half.
Sprinkle each potato cavity with pepper.
Combine sour cream, chopped olives, chopped tomatoes and hot pepper sauce in a small bowl.
Fill potato cavities with a dollop of sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with chives.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 24.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Take uncooked chicken off bones and cut into bite-size pieces. Salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in skillet on low heat.
Add all ingredients, except chicken.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top and push down with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Cover with foil and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Add grated cheese, if desired.
Heat just until melted.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together in 2nd bowl, flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
(Put 1/2 cup oats into blender and make a powder.)
Mix together all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Make golf ball size cookies; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes. Makes 112 cookies.
This is the original recipe.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except blueberries.
Mix well as you would any cake mix.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients and refrigerate.
Toss the items.
Add the last two ingredients at the last minute.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place meat in casserole.
Mix all other ingredients together; pour over meat.
Bake for 3 hours at 350°, covered.
Mash while hot.
Serve on buns.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, and peppers in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces.
Mix together salad dressing, sour cream and dry salad mix.
Add to vegetables and toss well.

title: 5 layer casserole
directions: Put in layers.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: dog biscuits(for man's best friend)
directions: Combine flours, yeast, bulgur, cornmeal, parsley flakes and milk in a large bowl.
In small bowl, combine yeast and warm water and stir until dissolved.
Add chicken broth.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients and mix well with hands.
Dough will be stiff so add more water if necessary.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut with knife or doggie bone cookie cutter. Transfer cut biscuits to cookie sheet and brush lightly with egg glaze.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Turn off heat and let biscuits dry out in oven overnight.
Yield:
6 to 7 dozen biscuits.

title: butter frosting for cake decorating
directions: Beat at low speed.
To thin, add water.
To thicken, add powdered sugar.

title: saucy green beans
directions: Place beans in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Cook, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: long island tea
directions: Mix and fill with Coke.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a medium bowl, using wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer. Reserve some for garnish.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently stir in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spoon over berries in crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and reserved berries.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: hoagie spread
directions: Chop all the meats and cheese into small pieces.
Shred the Lettuce, dice the tomatoes and onions.
Mix all the ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Spread on an Amoroso or any long or round sandwich roll.

title: sangria wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix well, then make into patties.
Place in a hot skillet with oil and fry until brown on both sides.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Delicious with vegetables or chips.

title: authentic french dressing(for bibb and leaf lettuce)
directions: Shake all ingredients together.
Serves about 4 salads.

title: hot tea
directions: Mix well; put 2 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.
Keep in tightly closed jar.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix together the oleo, eggs and sugars.
Blend in pineapple and bread pieces.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Superb with ham.
(Use Pyrex casserole dish.)

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Melt butter. Add garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce; stir well.
Let butter mixture cool, but not congeal.
Dip chicken in butter, then crumbs.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Add melted butter to sweet potatoes, then milk and sugar.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with floured cutter.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger and diced bacon; add and saute onions.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook on medium to low heat in large Dutch oven or heavy pot.
Add all seasonings.
Cook 1 hour, then add tomato paste and cook on low heat 30 minutes.
Add cooked beans and simmer for 30 more minutes.
Cook pinto beans in clear water until tender, not mushy, after washing and presoaking for 4 hours or overnight.

title: asparagus souffle squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish.
In a large bowl, beat eggs for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tester inserted near center comes out clean.
Let cool.
Cut into 36 squares.
Serve at room temperature.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice, adding enough water to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
In a saucepan, bring to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Break up cranberry sauce with a fork; stir into gelatin mixture.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in crushed pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into oiled mold.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crullers
directions: Dissolve soda in milk.
Strain it into 1/2 pint flour and melted butter.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Work them into rest of ingredients.
Add flour to make it stiff enough to roll out; cut and fry in hot lard or oil.
Flavor with nutmeg.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine and mix sugar, corn syrup and peanuts.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir in salt.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes or until light brown in color.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour immediately on buttered cookie sheet.
Break when cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Work butter into flour with fingers.
Add the rest of the dry ingredients and raisins.
Use fingers to do this.
When mixture resembles coarse meal, add egg beaten lightly with buttermilk. Stir with a spoon until well blended.
Dust hands with flour and knead dough for 3 minutes on a floured surface (will be smooth). Cut in half and shape into two balls.
Set on greased baking sheets and flatten slightly and cut a cross into the top with a sharp floured knife.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes until gold and crisp.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Add zucchini, flour, baking powder, soda and salt into egg mixture.
Add fruit and nuts and bake in two or three loaf pans or one angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: swiss steak for 2
directions: Cut steak into 2 pieces.
Salt, pepper and flour steak.
Brown in oil.
Add tomatoes.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Add green pepper, onion and salt.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches into buttered tin.
Sprinkle with sugar and dots of butter.
Place in warmed oven.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Cover peach mixture with flour mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Cool.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well by hand.
Cream in sugar.
Add dry ingredients, then chips and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: california sushi sauce
directions: Stir well.
May be used as a vegetable dip also.

title: itsy-bitsy pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Coat cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
Evenly sprinkle 1 tablespoon cornmeal on each sheet.
Cut dough into 6 equal pieces.
On lightly floured surface, roll each piece of dough into a 6-inch circle, using hands to stretch dough. Pinch edge of dough to form a low, stand-up rim.
Place 3 dough circles on each cookie sheet; brush each circle lightly with oil. Top pizzas as desired.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until crust is golden and cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Return to pan.
Add cheese; stir.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pickled onions
directions: Put onions in crock (glass) bowl.
Add salt; mix well.
Let stand 12 to 18 hours to cure.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Combine sugar and vinegar; let boil.
Pack onions in pint jars.
Add sugar and vinegar mixture to cover onions and within 1/4-inch of top.
Add 1 or 2 cloves per jar.
Wipe rim; add lids and submerge in boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: fudge goodies
directions: Mix brown sugar, softened butter, egg, flour, salt, milk and soda together.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup hot water to 1 square chocolate or 3 tablespoons cocoa and add vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture to first mixture.
Mix well, then pour in pan. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: nana georgia's prune cake
directions: Mix and stir all ingredients together with wooden spoon.
Bake in a buttered glass baking dish at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Sprinkle salt over onions and squash.
Put ice on top.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Mix the vinegar, sugar, seeds and turmeric. Heat well.
Add squash mix.
Bring to a full boil.
Fill jars and seal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all the ingredients and bake in 2 greased and floured bread pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: after dinner mint brownies
directions: *Three tablespoons of cocoa and 1 tablespoon oil equals 1 square unsweetened chocolate.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Can be stored in refrigerator.
Makes enough for 10 chicken halves.

title: something different sweet rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and flour.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups of hot water.
Let rise until double in size.
Roll into a rectangular shape on floured surface.
Spread with butter, cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Roll as a jelly roll and cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch slices.
Let rise in pan.
Before baking, melt topping ingredients: oleo, syrup, brown sugar and nuts.
Pour over rolls. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix with cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, cake coloring, margarine and eggs.
Blend until moistened.
Add soda and vinegar and mix into cake mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 375° in layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Blend 1/3 cup peanut butter with powdered sugar and vanilla. Using 1/2 teaspoon for each, shape into balls.
Combine melted Candiquick and 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Spoon just enough mixture into each of 24 paper bonbon cups (1 1/2-inch) to cover the bottom. Top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Chill for faster setting. Makes 24 cups.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add cake mix and sour cream.
In a separate bowl, mix chopped pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour half of the batter in a tube pan that is greased and floured well.
Add pecan mix on top of the batter, then add the remainder of the cake batter.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: ham and green bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse beans under running cold water to separate; drain and spread in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Layer with ham and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until golden brown, 45 minutes.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Roll out saltines on wax paper until finely crushed.
Add cut up dates and nuts.
Set aside.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and grate or put in food processor.
Add mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix all together.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve warm.

title: special chocolate cake with double frosting
directions: Combine cocoa, boiling water and butter, stirring until mixture is smooth; set aside to cool.
Combine sugar and next 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl; add cocoa mixture and shortening, beating at medium speed until blended.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes or until blended.
Pour batter into 3 waxed paper lined and greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove layers from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Spread never fail frosting between layers and on top of cake.
Spread chocolate frosting over top and sides of cake.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.
Yield one 3-layer cake.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion and green pepper in reserved drippings until tender, but not brown.
Drain, if needed.
Crumble bacon and mix with other ingredients.
Bake uncovered in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes
directions: Start with a layer of potatoes in the crock-pot, then add a few onions and a layer of cheese.
Continue repeating the layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour soup over and cook 7 1/2 to 8 hours on low.

title: peanut chocolate balls
directions: For candy, combine crackers, peanut butter and sugar. Stir together with melted butter.
Roll into ball and place on wax paper.
Stick toothpicks into each ball.

title: rave reviews cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Cook shrimp, crab, onions and tomato soup until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Place in mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Serve with crackers.

title: church supper potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, begin with a layer of shredded cabbage.
Add a layer of potatoes, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Add layer of onion rings, pepper rings and boiled egg slices.
Spread with mayonnaise.
Make other layers or until all ingredients are used. Top with thin layer of mayonnaise and sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Mix before serving.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: curry pineapple dip
directions: Cut pineapple in half and drain.
Blend first 4 ingredients and chill.

title: ham and cheese rolls(becky creel's)
directions: Combine ham, cheese, onions and mustard. Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of ham mixture in center of each triangle.
Bring tips of triangle together in center of ham and press edges together to seal.
Place on greased baking sheet. Combine water and egg.
Brush over rolls.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: crisp potato squares
directions: Melt bacon fat in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients; spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Dot with bacon fat or chopped fried bacon on top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 400°. Cut into squares and serve.
(Very good with pork chops.)

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Spread seeds on cookie sheet.
Pour remaining ingredients over seeds.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours stirring every 30 to 40 minutes. EAT!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown, at 375°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: marshmallow salad(better known as pistachio salad)
directions: In a very large bowl, mix pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip all together; mix it well, then add the box of pudding, mixing well again.
Spread salad in an oblong container.
Sprinkle walnuts on top, then add maraschino cherries in 2 long rows.

title: layered salad with sweet onions
directions: Break lettuce in small pieces.
Place in bottom of a large salad bowl. Cover with layer of green pepper, onion rings, peas, celery and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar and spices together. Smooth mixture over top of layered vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture. Refrigerate several hours. Sprinkle chopped peanuts on top before serving.

title: granola
directions: In a large bowl combine oats, apple and wheat germ; mix well.
In a small saucepan stir together honey, water and cinnamon.
Heat to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla or almond extract. Pour over oat mixture; mix well.
Spray a 15 x 10 baking pan and spread oat mixture evenly in pan.
Bake in a 325° oven about 45 minutes or until brown, stirring occasionally.
Spread onto foil to cool.
To store, place cooled granola in an airtight container in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: drop ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in molasses. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Test one cookie, if it cracks open, the dough is too stiff.
If the cookie flattens, the dough needs more flour.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: martha washington creames
directions: Add sugar a little at a time.
If it gets crumbly, add a drop of milk.
Flatten and roll into a ball.
Dip in chocolate.
Put a nut on top.

title: canned apples
directions: Wash and peel apples.
Slice.
Place an aspirin in bottom of hot, sterile jar.
Pack sliced apples in jar.
Cover apples with boiling water.
Place another aspirin on top of packed apples. You may also add Fruit Fresh, use as directed for brighter apples. Seal with hot lids.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large boiler.
Add water; cook until done. Remove chicken from broth.
Cool.
Bone chicken and cut meat into bite size pieces.

title: old fashioned cornmeal mush
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and stir into boiling water very slowly.
Turn down fire and cook slowly, stirring, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Eat warm with milk and sugar or lump of butter.
If desired, you may fry by pouring into an oiled loaf pan and store overnight.
The next day, slice and fry crisp in hot fat over hot fire.
Serve immediately with butter and syrup.

title: orange and avocado salad
directions: Peel avocados and cut into thin slices; dip slices into lemon juice to keep from turning dark. Peel oranges (navel) and cut into slices.

title: brow pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Spread batter evenly into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: mamere's apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix and lemon gelatin.
Add apricot nectar and oil. Add the eggs, one at a time, and vanilla and lemon flavorings. Bake in ungreased tube pan at 325° about 55 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.

title: strawberry whipped cream cake
directions: Beat yolks until thick; gradually add sugar, vanilla and then water.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch waxed paper-lined pan. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
When cool, cut in half.

title: purple passion cake
directions: Cook cake; let it cool completely.
Beat the cream cheese and gradually add powdered sugar.
Add the Cool Whip; beat well. Cover the cake completely.
Spoon on the blueberry pie filling. Let it run down sides of cake (may fill hole in center).

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a Pyrex oblong glass pan.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder together.
Pour this mixture over melted oleo. Then pour fruit over the 1st mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: coriander pork
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork.
Marinate pork in mixture for 30 minutes. Grill over medium-hot coals for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once.

title: kathy's brownies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add this to the flour mixture.
Pour into a greased pan, 8 x 8-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello with	1
cup boiling water. Let set slightly. Add pineapple and cranberries.	Cut in sour cream gently.
Add nuts if preferred.	Chill well.

title: green pepper relish
directions: Grind the peppers and onions into small pieces using a food grinder.
Add the salt and let mixture stand overnight.
In the morning, drain well and add the sugar and vinegar.
Cook the mixture 20 minutes or longer until the vegetables are soft and tender.
Spoon cooked relish into hot sterilized 1/2 pint jars. Cover with lids and process 5 minutes in hot water bath.
Remove from the water and let cool 24 hours before storing.

title: chili
directions: Drain meat, removing excess fat.
Put meat in roaster pan. Add seasonings to taste.
Cook onions in water; add to pan of meat.
Add tomato paste.
Drain beans and add to meat; mix well. Divide chili between two roaster pans.
Add enough water to make a medium texture of chili.
Not too thick, not too thin.
Heat oven to 350° and let simmer until piping hot, about 1 hour.
Serves 40.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pork, and simmer 1/2 hour or until thick.
Pour over pork which has had fat removed.
Stir and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: beef in potato shells
directions: Prepare and bake potatoes.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into halves.
Scoop up potatoes, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Brush outsides and insides of shell with margarine.
Place shells, cut sides down, upon ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until edges are brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown. Stir in tomatoes and seasoning mix.
(Break up tomatoes.)
Simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with cheese. Heat until cheese is melted in 475° oven.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with green onions.
Serves 6.

title: artichoke-aroni salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package.
Remove from heat; add finely chopped other ingredients.
Stir in mayonnaise and curry.
Serve cold or still warm.

title: english roast beef
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Season the roast with salt and pepper to taste.
Melt 2 Tbsp. butter in a dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Brown the outside of the roast on all sides in the butter.
After the roast is browned, add 1/2 c. water to the pan, and sprinkle 1/2 tsp. of sage, and 1/2 tsp. of mint onto the roast.
Place onion and garlic into the pan if desired, and season with seasoning salt and red pepper flakes, if using.
Cover the pot, and place the roast in the oven for 2 to 3 hours depending on how well done you prefer the meat to be; 2 hours for rare, and 3 for well done.
Removed finished roast to a pan to keep warm.
Melt 1 Tbsp. of butter in a medium skillet.
Whisk flour into melted butter until smooth.
Remove from heat, and stir in 1/2 c. cold water.
Mix until a smooth paste is formed.
Return to medium heat, and season with remaining sage and mint.
Stir in the liquid from the roasting pan and boil, stirring constantly until the gravy is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Slice the roast and serve with gravy poured over the meat.

title: angel lush
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple in medium bowl. Gently stir in whipped topping. Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.

title: easy and good brussels sprouts
directions: Par boil brussels sprouts until medium hard about 7-10 minutes. Fry bacon, onion and garlic until brown.
Add brussels sprouts to pan and mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste and saute 10 minutes.

title: rice the japanese way
directions: Cook rice.
In a large circular dish (Japanese rice tray), layer 1/2 of rice.
Next, add all of kombu which has been soaked and drained.
Layer remaining rice.
Sprinkle generous amount of Furikake and red ginger strips.
Great for parties!

title: one dish pork chop dinner
directions: Place skillet on medium high heat.
When hot, place pork chops in skillet and brown on both sides.
Do not flour.
When brown, add mushroom soup and sliced potatoes; cover and turn heat to low and cook about 45 minutes.

title: sweet trash
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler, then pour over mixture. Spread on wax paper; cover cookie sheet until hard then break up into pieces.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt 2 cups milk and margarine (don't boil).
Mix brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour together. Add remaining 2 cups milk.
Pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes until filling is firm.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In heavy pan, bring first three ingredients to a boil, stir well.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over cake while frosting is hot.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Combine fruit, 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in 1-quart baking dish.
Combine egg, sugar, milk and vanilla and beat until thick. Stir in mix and drop by spoonfuls over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is brown.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: quick as a wink
directions: Slice raw potatoes.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Crumble hamburger over potatoes.
Add cream of celery and cream of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove the foil the last 1/2 hour.

title: mystery cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg yolks; alternate dry ingredients and soup.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in square cake tin.

title: mother's day cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Beat 10x sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla until smooth.
(Add red food coloring if wanted.)
Slice layers in half and frost.
Add strawberries on top.

title: recipe for a loving family
directions: Mix all together gently.
The result will be a happy family full of love, peace, faith, trust, caring, forgiveness and sharing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, then add meat.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey bunnies(makes 15 bunnies)
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat evaporated milk, honey and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Butter does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
With spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make stiff batter.
Place in bowl coated with Baker's Joy; spray top of dough with Baker's Joy. Cover tightly with plastic; refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Put bacon (or ham or sausage), onion and cheese in pie shell. Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper (mushrooms) and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Stir-fry pepper, celery and onion in the oil in a large skillet about 8 minutes, until tender.
Add consomme and rice. Cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Blend in mushroom soup.
Pour into lightly buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Cover.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour or until rice is done and liquid has been absorbed.
Decorate, if you like, with pimento strips.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix sugar and water; chill.
Then mix juices and bananas. Take out sugar solution and mix together.
Divide and pour into two containers (ice cream buckets) and freeze solid.
Thaw for at least 2 hours until slushy.
Pour in punch bowl.
Add one 2 liter bottle ginger ale for each container.
Serves 48.

title: texhoma beans
directions: Cook beans in water and salt to taste.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons oil.
Brown meat; drain off grease.
Add beans, meat and remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Layer apples, apricots, pears, peaches and pineapple in a large bowl.
Combine orange juice and lemon juice.
Pour over fruit.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: dutch cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients well.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 (9-inch) cake tins.
Batter will be thick.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Then dot with butter, pushing butter down into the dough. You may add apples or blueberries to the batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
If you add fruit, bake 5 minutes longer.

title: three in one
directions: Saute pepper and onions in butter.
Add meat; cook until browned.
Place alternate layers of meat mixture and corn in buttered baking dish, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Arrange sliced tomatoes over top.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.
Serves 6.

title: jalapeno pickled peppers
directions: Boil pint jars 15 minutes.
Leave in hot water until ready to use.
Wash peppers. Cut peppers into rings. Fill each jar with cut peppers.
Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over peppers and seal.

title: fresh apricot pie
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apricots in a large bowl.
Add the sugar, tapioca and salt.
Mix gently to combine fruit and dry ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Roll out half the pastry and fit into a 9-inch pie pan.

title: butternut squash
directions: Slice squash in half lengthwise.
Place face down on a baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until flesh is tender and shell is firm enough to be stuffed.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese until blended.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Then add pecans and orange slices.
Regular Jell-O and Cool Whip can be used if preferred.

title: icebox fruit pie
directions: Mix together and pour into shells.
Put in icebox.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Add all ingredients in a big pot and heat on simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add 1 to 2 cups water, if desired.

title: boiled new potatoes with mustard and parsley
directions: Cook potatoes in a large pot of lightly salted boiling water until they are just tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine wine, mustard, oil, salt and pepper.

title: almost better than sex cake
directions: Make approximately 12 holes in the baked cake using a wooden spoon handle.
Pour the condensed milk over the holes.
Pour the 2 ice cream toppings over the holes.
Chill cake.
Just before serving, top with Cool Whip and crumbled Heath bars.

title: sausage bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Let 2 loaves frozen bread rise; pat in a cookie sheet until flat (like a pizza).
Fry sausage and drain well.
Mix chopped onion, green pepper, celery and grated cheese.
Spread on top of flattened bread dough; roll up and butter the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Add rest of ingredients. Place in casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse("the bomb")
directions: Mix both puddings together according to package directions. Bake devil's food cake according to package directions.
Use a square or rectangular pan to bake cake.
When cake cools, cut into squares.
In a large bowl, layer cake squares on bottom.
Next, add pudding layer, then Cool Whip layer.
Sprinkle top of Cool Whip with crushed Heath bars or Skor bars.
Begin another series of layers starting with cake and ending with Cool Whip and Heath bars. If you use pecans, sprinkle on top of candy bars.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine boiling water and oatmeal.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream butter and sugars, then add to oatmeal.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to oatmeal mixture and stir in vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured 11 x 13 pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients for icing and spread on cake. Brown under broiler until bubbly.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and honey.
Add apples; mix well to prevent apples from discoloring.
Add celery, walnuts and grapes; mix lightly.
Chill well before serving.
Yield: 3 or 4 servings.

title: tangy green beans
directions: Wrap 6 or 7 beans in each bacon strip and boil until bacon is done.
Mix butter, vinegars, salt, pepper, parsley, and onions together.
Boil and pour over beans.

title: e-z fudge
directions: Boil pudding mix, sugar and milk until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Add butter.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken, celery, almonds, pimento and mayonnaise.
Blend in lemon juice, onions and seasonings.
Fill a shallow, greased casserole.
Mix grated cheese with chips.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until heated through and lightly browned.
Yields about 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken until done. Cut into bite size pieces. Cook chicken broth, bouillon cubes and vegetables, that have been chopped in food processor, until soft. Put chicken in stock and add water until desired taste. Before serving, cook noodles. Put noodles in bowl and pour broth over noodles. Serve. Sure to make anyone feel good when tasting! Serves 6 to 8. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in greased casserole dish.
Combine soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into 3 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: basic red salsa
directions: Put all in blender; blend until desired consistency.
Stores well in refrigerator for several days.

title: hot and spicy chili
directions: Combine ground beef, onions and garlic in a large saucepan and cook until meat is browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, then lower temperature and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups vanilla chips and chocolate chips.
Microwave chips for 2 minutes.
Stir; microwave 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows, cereals and peanuts.
Mix spread evenly on 13-inch pizza pan that has been coated with Pam.
Arrange cherries on top. Sprinkle with coconut.
Melt remaining vanilla chips; add oil and stir until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza.
Chill until firm.
Serve at room temperature.

title: neiman marcus cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and
mix well.
Add chocolate chips, grated candy and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over cabbage. Sprinkle with rice wine.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a baking dish, layer rice and chicken; top with mixture of soup and milk.
Sprinkle with pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: orange butter whitefish fillets(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Mix salt, pepper, orange juice, orange rind, melted butter and nutmeg.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 450° allowing 10 minutes per inch thickness for frozen fish or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: connie's red beans
directions: Cut up bacon and fry with cut up onions.
Drain off grease. Cut up celery and green pepper.
Drain the kidney beans.
Combine these with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add orange juice, crushed pineapple, lemon juice and banana.
Makes 2 trays.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Add chilies and tomatoes. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese.
Keep hot in crock-pot.

title: cranberry raspberry pie
directions: Drain raspberries (press lightly) and reserve syrup.
Add enough water to make one cup.
In saucepan, combine cranberries and syrup mixture.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to cranberry mixture. Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in raspberries.

title: southern cooked beans
directions: Put washed beans in crock pot or in large pot on stove. Add water, salt and oil. Cook until partially done and add ham or ham hocks.
Cook until beans are tender. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit dip
directions: Thaw Cool Whip and mix all of the ingredients with fork. Refrigerate a couple of hours.
Serve with fresh fruit (strawberries, grapes, apples, pears, cantaloupe, cherries, etc.).

title: poulet a deux
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with slices of ham.
Place 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese in center of each.
Roll and secure with toothpicks. Arrange in baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, sugar, salt, Tabasco and garlic powder; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove toothpicks.
Place slice of Mozzarella cheese over each roll.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: favorite fillets
directions: Combine bay leaf, tomato sauce, mustard and mayonnaise in bowl.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Arrange fish in baking dish.
Pour sauce over fish and top with crumbs.
Microwave for 5 minutes; turn dish and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: ham salad filling
directions: Rinse frozen peas under running cold water to separate; drain. Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least two hours.

title: easy broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and bacon in large bowl.
Mix well. Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl; mix until sugar dissolves.
Chill both mixtures until 30 minutes before serving time.
Pour dressing over broccoli mixture; mix well.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Brown ground chuck with onions; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix. Spread mixture in a greased 10 1/2-inch pie plate.
Spoon drained chilies over meat mixture.
Mix eggs, milk and Bisquick until creamy; pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes.
Take out, put sliced tomatoes on top and sprinkle cheese over tomatoes.
Return to oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with sour cream.
Serve with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Note:
Kiwi fruit and grapes are also good added

title: quick potato cheese bake
directions: Prepare instant mashed potato as label directs. Preheat oven to 350°.
Add Parmesan to potatoes and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Spoon potatoes into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake slightly puffed and golden. Makes 6 or 7 servings.

title: peanut butter microwave fudge
directions: Put all ingredients except nuts in a 2-quart microwave dish. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add nuts and blend only once until smooth.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: meat loaf and sauce
directions: Mix above ingredients and form into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on pie shells.
Arrange 1/2 strawberries over cream cheese.
Mix sugar, cold water, cornstarch, syrup, butter and salt in a pan and bring to a boil. Cook until thick, 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in strawberry Jell-O and red food coloring immediately while hot. Chill until almost congealed before pouring over strawberries. Chill.
Before serving, top with whipped cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Measure and sift flour; add to first mixture.
Stir in remaining vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix well; mixture will be very stiff.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: three vegetable roast
directions: Peel, seed and chunk squash and potatoes. Brush with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° on a greased cookie sheet until tender.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together sugar, salt, shortening, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and cocoa.
Also add baking powder.
Add this to first mixture alternately with water and sour milk.
Add slightly more flour if milk is not thick.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake in a hot oven.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients, then pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Add vanilla to oil, honey, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
In
a large roasting pan, put the flakes, wheat germ, all-brand, nuts and seeds.
Pour honey mixture over all.
Put in oven at 300° for 10 minutes; take out and stir.
Repeat every 10 minutes for 45 minutes.
When cool, add 1 3/4 cups of raisins or any dry fruit and coconut.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Combine carrots, celery and carrot tops, cilantro, onion, chicken breast, garlic and stock in a large soup pot. Bring to a boil over medium high heat. Reduce heat and simmer, covered for 25 minutes or until chicken is tender. Heat oil in fry pan over medium high heat. Cut tortillas into 1/2 inch strips and fry to desired crispness. Drain on paper towel lined plate. Strain simmered soup into large bowl and slice cooked carrots from the strained vegetables. Discard other vegetables, if desired. Remove chicken breast and refrigerate covered, until cooled. Once cooled, shred meat and add to broth, refrigerate. Once completely cooled, skim off any fat. Ten minutes before serving, bring soup to a simmer over medium high heat. Peel avocado and slice. Add avocado, tortilla strips, tomato sauce, lime juice, additional cilantro if desired, and jalapeno chilies to soup and stir. Simmer 5 minutes and serve.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Place the chicken breast in the freezer for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
When the chicken is firm, remove the skin and cut into thin pieces, about 1/4 x 1-inch or cubes and set aside.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Combine cooked squash, margarine, onions, crushed crackers, beaten egg mixed with milk, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup of cheese. Pour into buttered casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° fo 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat well at medium speed.
Divide into 4 layers.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel and slice onions; separate into rings (about 5 cups). Saute in butter until golden, not brown (about 20 minutes).

title: meatball muffins
directions: Mix and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: almond cake with raspberries
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Thaw and drain raspberries.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper.
Butter paper.
Grind almonds and 1 cup sugar to a powder; combine with flour.
Melt butter.
Add Amaretto.
Beat white and salt until peaks.
Fold 1/4 of almond mixture at a time into whites, alternating with butter.
Pour into pan.
Gently push raspberries into top of cake.
Cook for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and mold. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: apple cheese bake
directions: Mix cheese, butter, sugar and flour with hands until doughy consistency.
Pour apples in 8-inch square pan, then spread cheese mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slightly cook carrots, drain and cool.
Crush Ritz and add to melted oleo.
Mix all ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes with brush.
Slice potatoes with skins on into about 1/2-inch slices.
Boil in water about 15 minutes.
Lay boiled slices into a greased 10 x 14-inch baking dish or pan.
Dot potatoes with remaining stick of oleo.
Liberally, sprinkle potatoes with garlic powder.
Add pepper to taste.
Mix 1 can of cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 can of milk (measured with same can).
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove potatoes from oven and spoon Cheez Whiz over top and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk.
Line the bottom of a large pan with whole vanilla wafers.
Alternate layers of pudding mixture and sliced strawberries.
Top with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: rave-bringing cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bread crumbs in butter until browned.
Set aside to cool.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Make pumpkin according to recipe on the can for 2 pies. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (Pyrex if you have one). Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle with margarine to cover dry cake mix.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; cool.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: graham squares
directions: Cool well before covering cooked bottom.
Then cover with 1 cup whipped cream sprinkled with graham cracker crumbs.
Keep in freezer.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together; store in jar.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: beef, cabbage and tomato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef
is crumbly;
drain.
Add tomato sauce, cinnamon, cloves and salt;
mix well.
Layer cabbage and ground beef 1/2 at a time
in 12
x
12-inch
casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: derek's awesome juice
directions: Put them all into the blender, blend around 4 minutes.
Pour it in a tall glass.
Try it!
It is very tasety.

title: brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla in medium bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well with a spoon or whisk.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread into medium-sized pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir beef over medium heat until brown; drain.
Stir in oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese. Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Spoon beef mixture over top.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab stew
directions: Cream butter
with flour, mashed hard-cooked egg yolks, mustard, salt, pepper
and	cayenne,
beating until mixture is smooth.
Slowly add
enough
hot
milk
to	make a thin paste. Pour paste into remaining hot milk and bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add
crab meat and heat 1 minute longer. Remove from heat and
add
sherry.	Place
a slice of lemon in each soup bowl.
Pour
in mixture and garnish with the chopped hard-cooked egg white and parsley.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Stir first six ingredients and mix together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Spread 4 crumbled crackers on top with grated cheese and bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: wheat and cheese snacks(diabetic)
directions: Crush cereal to 1/2 cup.
In a small bowl, beat margarine and cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in cereal and flour.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pueblo chicken and rice
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, tomatoes, onion, chillies and olives.
Spoon 1/2 into 2 1/2-quart dish.
Spread with chicken, 1/2 of sour cream and 1/2 of cheese.
Top with remaining rice mixture,
sour cream and Jack cheese.
Chill 24 hours.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 45 minutes (1 hour if chilled) or until hot throughout.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: yon mazetta
directions: Brown meat; add onions, celery and pepper.
Simmer soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add drained, cooked noodles to mixture.
Turn into large casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. This makes enough for 2 to 3 meals.
Freezes well; do so prior to baking.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring the sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Take from heat and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper.
Let stand for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 minutes at 325°.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add oats.
Add anything else you want; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make Jell-O and let cool.
Grind cranberries and orange. Combine with remaining ingredients and let set until it becomes juicy.
Add to cool Jell-O.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Mix cheese and crumbs in bowl. Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in cheese and crumbs mixture.
Place chicken in shallow dish sprayed with pam.
After dipping all chicken, if any crumbs are left over, pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Heat soup and stir in sour cream.
Pour over chicken or use as side dip for chicken.

title: cream pie
directions: Preheat oven at 350°. Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and salt; gradually add milk. Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat. Add small amount to egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mixture. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add butter and vanilla; cool slightly.

title: holiday stuffing
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet until browned.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Cook onion and celery in drippings in skillet until tender.
Combine sausage, cooked vegetables, sage, marjoram, bread cubes and parsley in large mixing bowl; blend well.
Stir in chicken broth to moisten. Season with salt and pepper.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add green beans and soup.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon mashed potatoes on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Boil dates, butter, molasses, white raisins, brown sugar and water for 3 minutes and cool.

title: old fashioned fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Shake in bag of flour with seasoning in it. Fry in electric skillet containing Crisco.
Cook until brown. Drain.
Put lid on skillet and cook 2 hours at 200°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook berries until they pop open.
Add strawberry jello. (Don't add water to jello.)
Stir berries and jello until mixed well; add sugar, pineapple and nuts.
Mix all together and pour in container and chill.

title: cabbage and ham hash
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion, cabbage and carrot in hot margarine until vegetables are tender.
Stir in ham, potatoes, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Spread mixture evenly in skillet.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, turning occasionally with spatula.

title: chicken magnifico
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of sauce into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover sauce with 1/2 pound uncooked noodles.
Lay 6 chicken breasts or 1 cut up chicken on top of noodles.
Cover with the rest of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dog food
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce, chopped tomatoes and add seasoning to flavor.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add can of corn (do not drain) and corn meal.
Let cook until corn meal absorbs liquid.
Add olives, if desired.
Lay cheese slices on top; let melt.

title: greek chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Marinate 5 to 10 minutes in mixture of oregano, pepper, lemon juice and salt.
Heat olive oil in skillet and saute minced garlic briefly.
Add chicken strips (and marinade if you want) and cook until just brown.
Serve over cooked rice with some steamed broccoli.

title: granny pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Fill with mixture of first 5 ingredients.
Top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: rotisseri kumbak sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a quart jar and shake. Keep in the refrigerator. Delicious salad dressing. Very good for boiled shrimp.

title: sinful salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water; add fruit.
Pour half of mixture in 13 x
9-inch
greased
dish.
Let jell, then top with sour cream and remaining jello mixture.
Let set.

title: cuban chicken
directions: Simmer chicken in oil 15 minutes. Remove. To pan, add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook
4 minutes. Add tomato sauce, potatoes, spices, wine, raisins and olives.
Add chicken. Simmer about 35 minutes (until done). Stir in frozen peas. Cook until peas are done (2 to 3 minutes).

title: *church cookout chili
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Put meat in crock-pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on high 1 hour; turn to low and cook 4 hours.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken
directions: In large roasting pan, melt butter in 375° oven.
Mix buttermilk with egg in a flat dish.
Combine flour, pecans, sesame seed and spices on wax paper.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk mixture, then coat with pecan mixture.
Place chicken, skin-side down, in melted butter.
Turn chicken to coat with butter and place skin-side up in one layer.
Place pecan half on each piece. Bake for 1 hour without turning.

title: southern cole slaw
directions: Mix and heat sugar, water and vinegar.
Set aside.
Then mix other ingredients.
Next, pour mixture (sugar, water and vinegar) over veggie mixture and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours. Drain and serve.

title: soup mixture
directions: Cook and drain all ingredients.
Add to tomatoes and bring to a good boil.
Add salt and before removing from heat, add sugar and lastly add soda.
Cook in pressure cooker 30 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage leaves in boiling water until tender. Mix rice, salt, meat, pepper and egg. Form meat mixture into balls and wrap cabbage leaves around them. Spread half of sauerkraut on bottom of Dutch oven; place a layer of cabbage rolls on top and spread remaining kraut on top. Add tomato soup and water; cover. Cook 1 hour and 30 minutes on top of stove. Makes 6 servings.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, mix paprika, caraway seed, onion flakes (crushed), dry mustard, lemon peel, thyme leaves, salt and ground red pepper.
Brush wings with melted butter and lightly pat paprika mixture on wings.
Place wings in a large open roasting pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender.

title: land o lakes caramel orange rind
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Place teaspoonfuls of orange marmalade in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well. Shape into ball and sprinkle with paprika.

title: pear pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and lemon rind in mixing bowl.
Prepare pears.
Arrange in layers in 9-inch pastry shell. Sprinkle sugar mixture over each layer.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Put crust over top with slits to release steam.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until pears are tender.

title: shortbread(a taste of scotland)
directions: Sieve
the
flour and add the sugar.
Rub in the butter and then work the mixture into a ball with a knife.
Butter a baking tray
and
then
spread in the mixture or press into a floured mold.
Bake
in preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until browned.
Remove
from oven.
Cut into squares from the tray and sprinkle with sugar.

title: curried chicken fruit salad
directions: Peel the orange over a bowl to catch the juices. Section and cut into pieces. Add the cooked macaroni, chicken and grapes. In a small bowl, combine yogurt and curry, then pour over macaroni mixture. Toss to coat.

title: sleigh ride
directions: Whip the cream with vanilla.
Mix coffee with sugar and chocolate.
Pour into mugs.
Place a generous dollop of whipped cream in each mug.
Garnish with candy cane.

title: onion rings
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Add milk, oil and egg; beat until smooth.
Separate onions into rings.
Dip each ring into batter.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes in 375° heated oil.
Turn, drain and sprinkle with salt.

title: christmas fruit balls
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and brown sugar.
Add dry ingredients, sifted and well mixed.
Add raisins, pineapple, cherries and nuts. Form into balls, about 1 teaspoon to each ball.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 15 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen balls.

title: fried turkey
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in plastic bag (this will coat more than one turkey).
Dry turkey inside and out with paper towels.
Coat turkey inside and out with mixture.
Let stand overnight or longer.
Heat oil to 325°.
Put heavy string through turkey and lower it slowly into oil.
Make sure turkey is covered with oil, breast up.
Do not exceed 350°.
Cook 4 minutes per pound.
Peanut oil may be strained and used over and over.

title: dean's butterscotch pie(for 2 pies)
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs and milk together, then separately mix white sugar, flour and cornstarch; then mix and add to mixture. Add vanilla and butter, then add 1 quart boiling hot water.
Stir and let thicken.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Stew chicken until well done.
Remove bones and grind or cut very fine so it won't be stringy.
Cover with rich broth.
Put in enough cracker crumbs to dissolve broth.
Add chicken and mix together.
Bake in a flat pan at 350° for 1 hour or until it thickens.
Serve on hot buns.

title: pumpkin upside-down cake
directions: Mix and pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn relish
directions: Place in saucepan and cook five minutes. Stir in a can of whole kernel corn mixed with chopped red and green peppers. Cool in refrigerator.

title: baked beans and bacon
directions: Mix beans, onion, pepper, Worcestershire, ketchup and syrup. Stir in brown sugar.
Take 3 slices bacon and cut into fourths. Lay aside.
Take remaining 3 slices and cut into bite size pieces. Mix bacon pieces and stir evenly into beans.
Take remaining bacon and cut into fourths.
Place on top of dish. Bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown onion, ground beef and fat.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and water.
Mixture should simmer for 1 hour.
If needed, more water can be added.
Serve over cooked spaghetti with 1 teaspoon of grated cheese sprinkled on top.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 9 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: joyce's joyful brownies
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 20-25 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: Mix on medium speed butter and sugar for a full 4 minutes. Stir in melted chocolate and vanilla. Beat eggs, one at a time, on high speed until well blended. Pour in baked pie shell. Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Broil chicken.
Remove skin and bones.
Layer broccoli and then chicken pieces.
Mix mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour in two pie shells (Mrs.
Smith's is a good brand).

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
In a large casserole dish, mix ground beef, refried beans, salsa and 1/2 of the cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Microwave or bake until cheese on top is melted.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Stir together thawed strawberries, eggs and vegetable oil. Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar and nuts. Add to strawberry mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick bread mix
directions: Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Place in 14 cup container and
seal.
Store
up
to
6 weeks at room temperature (6 months for freezer).
Use mix for biscuits, muffins, waffles, quick breads and cookies.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite sized pieces.
Break tortilla chips into bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Arrange chicken on top of chips.
Mix soups, tomatoes and onion.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mountaineer's fruit cake(prune cake)
directions: Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: berry delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter/oleo well and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust, then arrange strawberries in an even layer.
Prepare pudding and pour over berries.
Chill several hours, then top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with a few choice berries.

title: lamb barley soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add lamb, onions and celery.
Cook until lamb is light brown, stirring occasionally while cooking.
Pour off any fat.
Add some carrots, peas and potatoes and also bay leaves, barley, water, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat (275°) for about 45 minutes or until vegetables are done. Add parsley and mix well.
Serve while hot.

title: mallow-graham bars(makes 18 bars)
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, melt margarine.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in graham crackers, raisins and peanuts.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool 1 hour or until firm.
Cut into 18 bars. Store in an airtight container.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine and stuffing.
Put 1/2 of stuffing mix in casserole dish.
Mix cooked squash and other ingredients.
Put 1/2 of squash mix on top of stuffing; then stuffing, then squash, then rest of stuffing.
Bake about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: soda biscuits
directions: In large bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda with pastry blender or two knives cut into shortening; until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk all at once, just until dough clings together.
Knead lightly floured surface a few times.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick, cut with 2 1/2 inch round cutter. Place about 1 inch apart on cookie sheet and braise with butter. Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bonnie's beef wellington
directions: Brown steaks on both sides.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter and wine.
Defrost and roll out patty shells.
Place piece of meat on patty shell; add mixture of onion, mushrooms and wine to meat and wrap pastry around meat.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°. Serves 4.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan; mix together remaining ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup and spread remainder evenly on bottom of pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: gladys' sweet stuff
directions: Cook over low heat until tacky.
Water test to see if it is hot enough (put a drop of the mixture into a bowl of cold tap water; if it forms a ball that you can pick up, the mixture is ready!)

title: zucchini and whole wheat fettuccine
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain.
Steam zucchini in small amount of water over high heat for 3 minutes; drain and set aside.
Combine oil, butter (or margarine), garlic and basil in small saucepan.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes; do not brown garlic.
Toss fettuccine with zucchini, garlic-basil sauce, grated cheese and salt.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: peach melba pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place peach slices in bottom of pie shell.
Cream together sugar, flour, oleo and salt.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture and mix well.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 50 minutes. When knife is inserted in middle, it should come out clean.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease a 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheet; set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, salt and peanuts. Cook and stir over medium-low heat to 240° on candy thermometer. Add butter flavor Crisco and vanilla.
Continue to cook and stir until 300°.
Stir in baking soda.
Immediately pour onto prepared baking sheet; spread quickly into even layer, about 1/4-inch thick.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: easter dinner ham
directions: Place the ham in a baking pan. Bake at 325° for 45 min. Mix the jelly, dijon mustard, ginger, and brown sugar in a saucepan. Cook over low heat until the jelly melts, stirring occasionally. Remove the ham from the oven. Pour the mixture over the ham. Bake for 30 min. longer.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon (not crisp).
Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain butter beans only.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole (3-quart).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour tortillas.
Place equal portions on each of 5 tortillas and spread to cover.
Roll up each tortilla; refrigerate for awhile.
Remove from refrigerator and slice into 3/4-inch slices.
Serve with salsa.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add lemon rind, eggs and milk. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Place in well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Smaller pans, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gilda's green bean casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until done.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in Mason jar until ready to use.
To make, add 1 to 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Beat together first 8 ingredients.
Add soda to cold water; add to batter.
Mix in baking powder and flour.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 375° until done, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Whisk together the flour and salt. Rub the butter into the flour with fingertips until resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle the water over the mixture while tossing with a fork. Knead the dough for several turns on a lightly floured surface to bring it together. Shape the dough into a thick disk. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate at least 1 hour. To roll out the dough, place between 2 pieces of waxed paper and roll it out to a circle 2-inches bigger than the size of the pan. Fit the dough into a 9-inch lightly buttered pie plate. Fold the overlapping edge of the crust under the rim. Pinch a small piece of dough between your thumb and 1st knuckle of index finger, angling your hand slightly. Repeat around crust, putting your index finger into the depression your thumb just made. Keep the crust in refrigerator until ready to fill. If prebaking the crust, refrigerate at least 30 minutes before baking.

title: marsala baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika; stir well. Dredge chicken in
breadcrumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in a shallow baking pan, coated	with cooking spray.
Dot with margarine and bake, covered, at
for	30
minutes.
Pour wine over chicken.	Cover and
bake
minutes;
uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Serves 6.
Low in calories and fat grams.

title: high-note tenor hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl; mix in onion.
Add egg and milk; stir until just mixed.
Drop from teaspoon, several at a time, into deep, hot fat.
Cook until golden brown; drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: double chocolate treasures
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chocolate chips (I use the microwave).
Stir until smooth. Cool slightly.
Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add combined dry ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Stir in remaining chocolate pieces.

title: hog's head cheese
directions: Wash your cucumbers thoroughly and pack into jars.
Make a solution of a proportion of 2 cups salt to a gallon of boiling water.
Pour over cucumbers and place a saucer over the top of each jar (do not seal tightly).
Let stand for 1 week.
On the eighth day, drain and wash cucumbers.
Cut them into small chunks, thin slices or spears.

Make a solution of one gallon hot tap water and 1 tablespoon powdered alum and pour over the pickles which you should put back into the cleaned gallon jar (do not pack tightly because the alum will make them swell).
Drain the water off the pickles for the next 3 mornings and make a fresh solution of alum and water to pour over the pickles.
Alum makes the pickles crunchy.
On the twelfth morning, drain all the water off the pickles.

Heat 6 cups white vinegar, 6 cups sugar and a mixture of 1 tablespoon pickling spice and 1 tablespoon celery seed; (put the spices and celery seed on a clean cloth and tie it so that the spices do not get into the vinegar).
Bring to a boiling point and pour over the pickles.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Combine bacon, broccoli, cauliflower and Cheddar cheese.
Mix separately the mayo, onion, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together the jello and cottage cheese.
Add the pineapple and oranges.
Chill.
Add the Cool Whip before serving.

title: killer brownies
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box in a 9x13-inch pan.
When done remove from oven.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix 1 bag (6 oz.) chocolate chips and peanut butter in pan on top of stove until melted. Remove from heat, add rice krispies.
Mix well - Spread on top of brownies.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Take 1 1/2 times the crumb recipe for best results.
Sift first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add egg; mix with fork.
Press half of crumb mixture into greased pan. Spoon cherry pie filling over first layer.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Serve warm topped with whipped cream, cold milk or ice cream.

title: maple pecan chiffon cake
directions: Do not grease pan.
Into a small mixing bowl put flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in brown sugar.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, cold water and maple flavoring.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugars and cinnamon.
Wet hands and cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll biscuits in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop into greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle remaining sugar over biscuits and pour melted butter over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rissotto with porcini mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in a deep skillet.
Grind in pepper to taste.
Add the rice.
Stir thoroughly.
Add wine.
Let some evaporate; add the broth.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Add milk and flour.
Blend well.
Add coconut.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and milk. Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Fold in creamed mixture.
Divide into 1/2 and chill for at least 1 hour.
Roll out and use cookie cutters or just use spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Enjoy plain or with Buttercream Icing.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar; add beaten egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat the flour mixture into the creamed mixture.
Shape dough into two rolls. Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate about 3 hours.
When ready to bake, preheat oven to 350°.
Cut rolls into slices and bake on slightly greased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, basil, Accent and pepper.
Mix together soy sauce, catsup, honey, corn oil and garlic.
Put chicken in baking dish and baste with sauce. Bake at 350° uncovered, basting frequently, for about one hour or until fork can be inserted with ease.

title: morning mix-up
directions: In a large skillet, saute potatoes, ham and onion in oil for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. In a small bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper. Add to skillet; cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set. Remove from heat and gently stir in cheese. Spoon onto a serving platter; sprinkle with chives.

title: caramel fudge balls
directions: Chop 1/2 cup of the walnuts to medium size pieces.
Chop remaining walnuts into fine pieces for coating fudge balls.
Melt butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugars, salt and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugars dissolve. Cover; boil slowly 5 minutes.
Uncover; cook rapidly without stirring to 236° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture is creamy and begins to hold its shape.
Stir in medium size walnut pieces.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Quickly shape into balls. Roll in finely chopped walnuts.
Let stand until firm.
Makes 24 balls.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese in bowl, add Bisquick small amount at a time and mix with hands.
Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make dressing first--Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; add raisins, onion and bacon.
Chop enough broccoli to fill 2-3 quart bowl.
Mix together.
Chill.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and oil in double boiler.
Stir in peanuts. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: lentil soup
directions: Put lentils in pan with enough water to cover.
Add vegetables and cook until lentils are tender.
May be served as is or with cooked elbow macaroni.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add carrot, leek and garlic; cook until tender, but do not brown.
Add stock; bring to simmer. Add broccoli; cook 8 to 10 minutes, until broccoli is tender. Pour soup into food processor; process until vegetables are finely chopped but not pureed.
Pour back into pot.
Add cream, pepper and celery seed.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat, add flour, salt and both peppers, stirring until smooth.
