Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in horseradish and lemon juice.
Cook until sauce is thoroughly heated.
Serve hot with corned beef or roast beef.

title: pumpkin cheesecake balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl on low speed mix cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice until crumbly. Press into bottom of 15 x 10-inch pan.
In another bowl mix cream cheese, milk, 2 eggs, pumpkin, spice and salt.
Pour over crust. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Chill and cut.

title: black-bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar, salt and chocolate chips in a mixing bowl.
Mix.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add flour and sugar.
Mix. Add salt and orange peel. Scald milk and add to egg mixture. Add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix sour cream and seasonings.
Chill.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Lightly mix cabbage with apples.
Pour sour cream mixture over cabbage mixture just before serving.
Toss lightly. Serves approximately 100.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed, beating after each addition. Bake at 325° in three layers (about 25 minutes).

title: date nut bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix in other ingredients with a fork.
Pour into a well-greased 8-inch pan.
Put into a preheated 350° oven and bake 25 minutes.
Allow to cool and roll in confectioners sugar after cutting into squares.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes with chocolate icing
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Mix buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately; mix well.
Roll out on floured cloth and cut.
Bake at 375° on foil-covered cookie sheet until lightly browned.

title: mother's jello salad
directions: In bowl, empty Jell-O and pour boiling water over it.
Stir until dissolved.
Set aside.
Mix pineapple, lemon juice and sugar in small saucepan and bring to boil.
Stir pineapple mixture into Jell-O.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken around edges.
Whip the cream and add to Jell-O.
Stir in cheese and place back in refrigerator.

title: beef-tomato-cabbage scallop
directions: Brown ground beef in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Then add onion and celery and cook for 10 minutes.
Add can of tomatoes, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
In buttered 2-quart baking dish, alternate layers of chopped cabbage and meat mixture, putting in layer of cabbage first, ending with a layer of meat mixture on top.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chips and oleo; add nuts.
Combine in bowl, flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Add chocolate mixture and stir carefully.
Put into foil paper baking cups that are set into muffin pans.
These must be baked in paper foil cups. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Yields 24 cupcakes.
Cool before serving.
They have a crunchy top and need to frosting.

title: shrimp crab au gratin
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add half and half and milk. Cook and stir until thick and smooth. Stir in lemon juice, crab meat, shrimp, water chestnuts, rice, pimento and 1/2 of the cheese. Spoon into large baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until mixture is hot.

title: cranberry sour cream crumble coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle chopped almonds in bottom of greased 10-inch tube pan. Set aside.
In bowl stir all topping ingredients until crumbly. Set aside.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Layer ingredients 2 or 3 times.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in sprayed pan.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Mix mushroom soup with milk. Add onions to taste. Top with Cheddar cheese. Shred potatoes for 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all together, then put into pan.
Top with cheese. Bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: thin white sauce(soup base)
directions: Melt butter. Add flour and blend. Add milk and salt. Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chicken delights
directions: Put rice in buttered 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Place chicken on rice. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix soup, milk and water; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook, uncovered, in crock-pot for 8 hours on low.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in salt and flour.
Add food coloring.
Mix until well blended. Using a cookie gun, form the cookies into desired shapes about 1-inch apart on a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until cookies are just beginning to turn brown.

title: herb baked chicken
directions: Spray a 2-quart oblong baking dish with vegetable cooking spray; arrange chicken, bone side down in dish.
Sprinkle with thyme and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach chicken
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, then pack in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Dip chicken in butter and flour and place on top of spinach. Season with salt, pepper and garlic. Pour whipped cream on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Heat ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine all ingredients in a large, ovenproof dish and stir, using enough ketchup to mix, but not soupy.
Parmesan cheese may be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° until mixture is hot and begins to bubble.

title: meat marinade for shish-kebabs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
For 2 pounds of cubed meat, 4 to 5 servings.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a pan.
Stir in next four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and sugar is completely dissolved.
Continue to cook without stirring until temperature reaches 260° or until a hard ball is formed in cold water.
After boiling has ceased, cool down. Stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Grease hands and pull until it has a satin-like finish and is light in color.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar, cinnamon and water.
Place in a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Cream shortening.
Add brown sugar and flour. Cream good. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
(Soak in cold, salted water to remove any bugs.)
Parboil in salted water for 10 minutes; drain water immediately to stop cooking.
In a small bowl, break and slightly beat the egg, milk and pinch of salt.
In another bowl, place the bread or cereal crumbs.
Dip cauliflower into egg mixture; coat well, then dip into crumbs.
Cover well.
Fry in oil or shortening until brown, turning to brown all sides.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes. Boil in water until tender (about 15 minutes). Drain and cool. Chop boiled eggs and add to potatoes; add pickles and bell pepper. Mix with mayonnaise gently. If desired, add celery and onions. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine.
Put Rice Chex into large bag.
Pour melted mixture over cereal.
Shake in bag until coated. Pour 1 pound powdered sugar into bag and shake to coat.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup and cook 4 minutes at 100% power. Add peanuts and cook another 3 1/4 to 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook for one more minute.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour and spread quickly on greased, flexible baking sheet.
Cool for 30 minutes and break into small pieces.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, onion and stock in soup kettle. Simmer, partially covered, for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Slowly add milk, stirring with a whisk until smooth.
Stir in cheese and cook over low heat until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Slowly add to veggies and stock.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Best served in bread roll bowls.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend well and pile in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: low-cal sundae
directions: Fills 5 or 6 cup-type dessert dishes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Arrange biscuits in a single layer in the bottom of a hotel pan.
Drizzle reserved strawberry syrup over biscuits and let set 1 hour.
Prepare mousse according to package directions and gently fold strawberries and Oreo pieces into prepared mousse.
Pour into reserved hotel pan.
Cover and chill until set.

title: slush
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze. Thaw until slushy to serve.

title: hawaiian beef and rice - luau
directions: Combine all ingredients for the marinade and pour over the roast.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours, turning several times.

title: easy chicken-rice supper
directions: Heat margarine in a 2-quart saucepan until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole or rectangular 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until bubbly, 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, each containing 315 calories and 16 grams fat.

title: ingrid's gingersnaps
directions: Heat syrup, sugar, butter and cream to boiling.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and let stand overnight.
Roll out very thin. Cut into diamond shape and brush with egg whites and a split almond on the top.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes, approximately. Watch closely as they burn easily.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except egg whites, after removing bones from salmon.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in casserole and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy hot chili
directions: Cook meat until browned.
Mix all ingredients together in a large pot.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat together.
Mix other ingredients.
Put in oven at 350°, long enough to melt cheese.
Layer of chips, meat, cheese, chips, meat, cheese.

title: graham cracker icebox pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and milk. Cook over hot water until eggs are done, not thick, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Alternate layers of crumbs and custard. Start and end with crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples with 4 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Beat eggs gradually adding 2 cups sugar, then mix oil in well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder, then add egg mixture gradually, alternating with orange juice.
Add vanilla.
Pour half the batter in, then place some apples.
Add remaining batter and end with apple slices on top.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer one crust in bottom of casserole.
Add filling.
Put other crust on top and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks margarine, sugar and eggs; beat 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Drain juice off pineapples and spread over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Nuts and cherries may be used to garnish.

title: garden dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, allow cream cheese to soften. Stir in tomato soup; add celery, onions, parsley and horseradish and mix well. Add dash of garlic, salt, pepper and sauce; blend well. Store in refrigerator in a covered container for several hours or overnight.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill for several hours. Shape into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans, dried beef or toasted almonds.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-o in hot water. Melt marshmallows in pot over low heat. Cool. Add ice water, pineapple and nuts. Add cool whip or dream whip to taste. Chill.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix to form crumbs and spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order and bake in a well-greased Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and turn out onto a plate.
Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix cocoa, water, syrup and salt.
Cook, stirring often, until mixture becomes a heavy syrup.
Stir in margarine and vanilla. Serve hot or cold.
If desired sweeter, add honey to taste after sauce has finished cooking.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In medium skillet, over medium-high heat, cook chicken until browned.
Set aside.
Add soup, water, garlic powder, pepper, and vegetable combination.
Heat to boil.
Add noodles.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes stirring often.
Return chicken to pan. Cook 5 minutes or until noodles are done, stirring often.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Break noodles in small pieces. Mix with cabbage and onion. Combine salt, pepper, oil, sugar, vinegar and flavor package. Pour mixture over noodles and cabbage. Stir and refrigerate overnight.

title: lollipops
directions: You also need 18 sticks.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Serve.

title: eleanor nabak's german potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes and veggies.
Take bacon, seasoning, sugar, vinegar, bacon grease and a little cornstarch and mix over low heat.
Serve warm.

title: oven chicken and gravy
directions: Cut chicken lengthwise into strips. Place chicken in melted butter in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Place the peeled tomatoes, onions, peppers, sugar, vinegar and salt in a dishpan. Cook until thick, about 2 hours.
Put this into jars and seal.

title: caramelized peanuts
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy skillet.
Cook until all peanuts are completely coated and no syrup is left.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and spread so that peanuts are separated.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring several times.

title: apple cinnamon cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend completely. Press on bottom and an inch up the sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except soda and popcorn in a 2-quart microwave dish.
Bring to a boil (3 minutes on High).
Stir and then cook 2 minutes more on High.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.
Stir until foamy.
Put popped corn in brown paper bag. Pour syrup over corn, close bag by folding top.
Shake and place bag back in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake; then cook another 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.

title: kaylee's favorite cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and Crisco in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed; mix until blended.
Divide dough into 4 quarters.

title: silly putty
directions: Will also need 5 ounce paper cups, popsicle stick (for stirring rod), paper towels and plastic bag (zip-lock or twist tie).

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese melts.
Serve on rye bread or crackers.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Into heavy kettle, put first four ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil until syrup spins a thread; add peanuts.
Stir and cook until mixture just begins to brown.
Remove from heat; stir in soda.
When soda is well mixed and mixture still foaming, pour into shallow 8 x 12-inch pan or cookie sheet; do not spread.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix raw peanuts, sugar and white Karo and boil over medium heat in boiler until honey colored and peanuts begin to pop. (Hard crack stage on candy thermometer.)
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Beat vigorously.
Work fast and pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread thin and allow to cool.
Break into desired pieces.

title: gingersnap pumpkin pie
directions: Combine milk and pie filling in a large bowl.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened. Stir in whipped topping, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze overnight or until firm.
Remove from freezer and let stand for about 20 minutes before serving.
Garnish with dollop of whipped topping.
Makes 8 servings.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Season round steak with salt and pepper. Cut into serving pieces and place in crock-pot with sliced onion.
Add potatoes, green beans and garlic. Top with soup and tomatoes.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 4 to 5 hours). If too much liquid has collected, remove cover and turn to high during the last 1/2 hour.

title: italian skillet dinner(serves 8 - 10)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse and drain well.
Brown sausage in large skillet; drain grease, then add ground beef and brown it; drain grease.
Saute onions until clear. Add spaghetti sauce, seasoning and cooked pasta and heat until bubbly.
Top with cheese and heat until cheese melts.

title: strawberry-banana smoothie
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Add milk and mix well.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon; mix well. Add oatmeal and chocolate chips; mix well.
Drop onto an ungreased cookie sheet; don't mash down.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: cranberry refrigerator cake(serves 12)
directions: Mix together cranberries, banana and granulated sugar. Set aside. Place 1/2 of wafers in bottom of pan.

title: play dough for kids
directions: Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture gets very thick.
Cool and knead.
Store in a plastic covered container.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a 4-quart pot, boil meat with salt, 2 whole ribs of celery, whole onion and whole potato very slowly for 3 hours or longer. Take soup meat from pot and remove meat from bone, chopping to bite size and discarding bone and fat.

title: korean barbecued beef(4 servings)
directions: Cut beef diagonally across grain in 1/8-inch slices.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in beef until well coated.
Cover; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Drain beef; stir-fry in 10-inch skillet or wok over medium heat 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice, if desired.

title: baked potato slices
directions: Combine soup, paprika and pepper.
Spray 2-quart rectangle baking dish with Pam.
Arrange sliced potatoes in baking dish overlapping rows.
Spoon soup mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes.

title: stuffed potato
directions: Slice potato in half longways.
Cut out potato on one side of sliced potato.
Mix butter, salt, pepper, garlic, green pepper and onion together.
Place in open shell of potato skin for each potato.
Close together with other 1/2 potato; wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour until potato is done.
Eat alone or with steak.

title: salmon crunchy salad loaf
directions: Mix chilled ingredients together, except the chips and chill. (It's better to add lemon juice to mayonnaise before adding to salad.)

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Dredge spareribs in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in fat.
Add onion.
Combine ketchup, Tabasco sauce, chili powder and hot water in a bowl.
Pour over meat; cover.
Place over low heat and cook until tender.

title: epiphany cake
directions: This cake is served during Epiphany following Christmas.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: best coconut cream pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add as much coconut as you like.
Pour into a pie crust that has been baked and cooled.
Brown some coconut in oven and add to top of pie.
Cool in refrigerator before serving.

title: frozen fruit drink
directions: Mix in blender and enjoy.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, vinegar and salt.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and optional ingredients, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: civitan fruit cake cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Dice fruit cake into 1/4-inch pieces.
Set aside.
(Dices easier if cold.)
Mix cake mix, oil, flavoring and eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Add the fruit cake pieces.

title: butter rum rolls
directions: Roll frozen dough in melted margarine.
Let rise (2 1/2 hours).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and glaze with melted sugar, water and rum.
Drizzle mixture over top. Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: popeye's spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed on box.
Drain and press all water from spinach.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Split 1 loaf French bread lengthwise; top half (about 1/4) and hollow out the middle of the bottom half.
In bite size pieces, place bread in a separate bowl.
Pour mixture into bottom half of bread.
Use bread pieces to dip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In salad serving bowl, mix sugar, lemon juice and mayonnaise together until smooth. Add broccoli and toss to coat well. Add remaining ingredients and toss to mix. Refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: adam's pear pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except oleo and divide evenly between the pie shells. Dot oleo pieces over top of filling.
Cover with top crust.
Score top crust with knife to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 450° until crust is lightly browned, about 10 to 15 minutes. Turn temperature down to 350°.
Bake until juice bubbles out top and looks thick (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: key west bollos(black-eyed pea fritters; boy-o's)
directions: Cover peas with water and soak overnight.
Remove skins by rubbing between hands.
Cover beans with additional water in another bowl and skins should rise to the surface; drain.
Combine peas, garlic, hot sauce and salt in work bowl of food processor or blender, adding small amount of water to keep mixture moving. Process until mixture has a fine consistency.
Beat mixture by hand until it is like cake batter.
Heat oil to 365°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Turn to brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Test for doneness and should look like hush puppies. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
Bollo mix is always best if made a day or two ahead to allow flavors to marry, getting all the work out of the way.

title: apple pie "no sugar"
directions: Heat apple juice and then add cornstarch.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, walnuts and raisins.
Stir in 4 cups of sliced apples.
Pour in pie crust and place lattice on top.
Place on hot cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel fruit, reserve as much juice as possible in a shallow baking dish.
Slice oranges and halve slices; cut grapefruit into segments and pineapple into chunks.
As each fruit is completed, place in a layer in a clear or cut glass bowl.
Sprinkle each layer with sugar.
Pour reserved juices over layers.
Cover; chill 1 hour or more.
Scatter cherries over fruit.

title: frozen egg nog
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and salt until it is thick like custard.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and heavy cream.
Whip it and freeze.

title: pineapple delight(12 servings)
directions: Mix together dry cake mix and whole can of pineapple - including juice.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 35-50 minutes until golden brown or cracks appear dry.
Bake at 350.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet, brown onion lightly.
Add green pepper, beef and rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to boil. Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: texas fudge(not candy)
directions: Shred all cheeses.
In a greased casserole dish, place cheeses and beaten eggs.
Toss until cheese is covered with egg.
Add jalapeno slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into squares.
Place on Triscuits; top with 1/4 teaspoon salsa.
Serve warm.

title: cucumber-onion pickles
directions: Wash, peel and slice cucumbers and onions.
Cover them with salt and let stand overnight.
Bring vinegar and salt to a boil. Sift together mustard, turmeric and cornstarch.
Mix with a little cold vinegar and add to vinegar and sugar.
Drain cucumbers and onions from salt water.
Put in vinegar solution and bring to a boil.
Pack in sterilized Kerr jars and seal at once.

title: old testament justice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks, honey, milk and 3 cups of the flour with the spices and baking powder, sifted into flour.
Use remaining 1/2 cup.
Pour to add to fruit.
Add beaten egg whites and flour mixture.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: southern almond bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat in the eggs and almond flavoring.
Add flour and salt.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds and cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out, cut into squares and put back into oven.
Bake another 5 minutes, or until light brown on top.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix dough and roll out thin;
grease pan and cut strips to line bottom.
Add cherries, sugar, salt, 3/4 cup juice, and butter.
Cut strips and cover top.
Cook at 400 degrees until brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Crisp bacon, reserving the fat.
Crumble the bacon.
Saute onion in bacon grease; add salt, sugar, mustard, water, vinegar, sliced potatoes, bacon and parsley last.
Heat to serve.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs and Ranch dressing mix; coat chicken with melted butter.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: upside down cornbread
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper until brown, and stir in flour.
Mix in tomato paste, salt, and pepper.
Remove from heat, stir in cheese.
Spread in 9 inch pan.
Cover with prepared corn bread mix.
Bake
(as directed on Jiffy cornbread mix box) 30 - 35 minutes in preheated oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and form into small loaves.
Place in an 11 x 13-inch covered dish.
Pour sauce over loaves and bake covered in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes of baking time.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour in a 6-cup mold.
Chill.
tags: Thank You lite cherry pie filling

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add pre-mixed dry ingredients.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water. Bring to a boil. Add peanuts. When peanuts smell or turn light brown remove from heat. Stir in soda. Mix well. Pour on cookie sheet lined in foil.

title: hot crab dish
directions: Mix crab and eggs.
Blend remaining ingredients into mayonnaise and stir into crab mixture.
Pour into greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.

title: dried fruit compote
directions: Place dried fruit, cinnamon sticks and water in large saucepan. Bring to boil, turn down heat to moderate simmer.
Cook until water is absorbed.
Stir in honey to taste.
Combine cashew nuts and water to cover in blender.
Blend and add water or nuts until cashews are a whipped cream consistency.
Place fruit in compote and top with big dollop of cashew whipped cream.
Fruit may be served warm or cold.

title: incredible french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch strips.
In large bowl, whisk together egg white, chili powder, salts, garlic and onion powder until frothy.
Add potatoes; toss to coat well.

title: bourbon burgers
directions: In medium bowl, soak croutons in bourbon until all liquid is gone, making sure croutons are completely saturated and soggy.
Add ketchup and beef and mix well.
Form into patties.
Place on medium-hot grill.

title: angel hair with savory tomato sauce
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, heat oil.
Add garlic.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Toss hot pasta with sauce.
Serve with cheese.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground chuck with celery, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain; add remaining ingredients to meat.
Cook for 1 hour on low heat.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
In saucepan combine water, oleo, cocoa and Crisco oil; bring to a boil.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and baking soda.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In a plastic bag, combine the flour, salt and pepper; shake to mix.
Add the chicken; shake to coat lightly.
Remove the chicken; reserve the excess seasoned flour.
In a large skillet, warm 1 tablespoon of the oil over medium heat.
Add the chicken; brown on one side for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining tablespoon oil.
Turn the chicken; brown well on the second side, about 5 minutes longer.
Transfer the chicken to a plate; set aside.
Coarsely chop onion.
Add the margarine to the skillet.
When the margarine melts, add the onion and cook, stirring, until softened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in the reserved seasoned flour and cook, stirring, until the flour is completely incorporated, about 1 minute.
Add the broth, 2 tablespoons of the lemon juice and the thyme; bring the mixture to boil, stirring constantly.

title: "dump cake"(yield: 16 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in a small saucepan over medium heat. Cook, stirring often, 5 minutes or until no calorie sweetener dissolves.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins.
Mix together remaining 3 ingredients and mix with the carrot mixture.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder.
Spread evenly in a 9 or 10 inch pie dish.
Spread sauce over top, then sprinkle with onions, pepper and pepperoni.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and bake for 5 more minutes until cheese melts.

title: ditalini with pesto, beans and broccoli rabe(4 servings)
directions: Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water 3 minutes. Add broccoli rabe and boil until broccoli rabe is just crisp-tender and pasta is just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes longer. Drain pasta and broccoli rabe, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid. Return pasta and broccoli rabe to pot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup, and part of crushed onion rings in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed onion rings or place whole onion rings on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: diabetic sugarless peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and flatten with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in an 8-inch square pan.
Stir well.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Let cool.
Combine strawberries, sugar, lemon juice and egg whites. Beat at high speed about 8 to 10 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip. Press 2/3 of brown sugar mixture in a 9-inch pan and pour in strawberry mixture.
Put remaining crumbs on top and freeze until firm.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Soak in ice water 30 minutes.
Prepare batter ingredients.
Dip in batter.
Fry 2 to 5 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice with water, salt and stick of margarine according to package directions.
Mix remaining ingredients all together and bake uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hamburger-macaroni casserole
directions: Make macaroni as directed on package.
While this is cooking, brown your hamburger meat with bacon, enchilada seasoning and winter garden seasoning blend.
After all of this is cooked, drain, rinse and add to cooked hamburger meat.
Add tomato paste and can of water.
Stir over low heat about 5 minutes.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Put cheese over this.
Bake at 350° until cheese is well melted.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice with cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter.
Place sliced apples in unbaked pie crust and pour apple juice mixture over apples.
Add top crust.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil last 20 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Sift together all other ingredients and gradually add to the milk mixture; beat until batter is smooth. Heat deep oil to 375°.
Hold finger over the hole of a funnel, which has a hole dimension of 3/8 to 1/2-inch.
Fill funnel with batter.

Hold funnel as near surface of oil as possible, remove finger and drop batter into oil, using a circular movement from center outward to form a spiral cake, about 3-inches in diameter. It takes practice, remember to place finger on bottom of funnel as you form each cake.
Form as many in skillet as will float uncrowded.
Fry until cakes are puffy and golden brown, turning once.
Remove cakes with slotted spoon to a paper towel to drain. Sift lightly with powdered sugar with a little cinnamon added. Serve at once.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sift cornstarch and sugar together.
Add syrup, eggs, butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add water.
Knead until dough is soft and elastic like bread dough.
If sticky, add a little more flour.
Pinch off approximately 8 to 10 balls, then roll out with floured rolling pin.
Cook on ungreased cast-iron skillet or griddle on medium-high heat.

title: applesauce cake *
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in tube pan lined with foil. If cooking too fast, place pan of water above cake for last 1/2 hour.

title: crab mold
directions: This recipe is best when made the day before you plan to serve it.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water. Melt cheese with soup; add remaining ingredients except crackers.
Pour into mold and let sit overnight.
Unmold; serve with crackers.

title: sister's cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for
to 15 minutes.
(Take them out of oven when they puff and go flat.)

title: grandma knight's fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Chill for about 1 hour.
Great for dipping apples, grapes, bananas, strawberries, etc.

title: fifteen minute meat loaf
directions: Combine the beef, salt, pepper, onion, green pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Press into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake on the lowest shelf in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes. Broil 5 minutes more.
While meat is cooking, combine remaining tomato sauce, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes.
Add meat drippings if desired.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Blend butter, eggs, brown sugar and molasses together.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Add to mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and spread on bun.
Put 1 slice cheese and 1 slice ham on each bun.
Wrap in foil.
Heat in oven 15 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: cake waffle cookies
directions: Combine melted margarine and eggs.
The add flour, baking powder and lemon extract.
Make sure the waffle iron is hot.
Drop 1/2 tsp. of batter on each waffle iron grid.
Bake about 30-45 seconds.
Should be light golden, not brown.
Take off with large fork.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cookie should be soft.
Makes 3-4 doz.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy and smooth and pour into pan that has been sprayed with Pam or Mazola cooking spray.
Bake in 300° oven for 60 minutes.
Should be light in texture and golden brown.

title: coconut-buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter.
Add buttermilk and coconut. Bake in 9-inch shell at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: sponge candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar in heavy kettle.
Use a candy thermometer and boil (medium heat) to 300°.
Mixture will look as if it is going to burn.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
(It is best to sift the soda; lumps will not break with stirring.)
Immediately start stirring very, very quickly and pour mixture into a thoroughly buttered 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Allow mixture to cool for at least 4 hours, then break or cut into pieces and dip in melted chocolate.

title: cheddar dill scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except butter, eggs and half and half.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir eggs and half and half in just until moistened. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth (1 minute).
Divide dough in half; roll each half into 8-inch circle. Cut each circle into 8 pie shaped wedges.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 16 scones.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 12-cup muffin pan.

title: onion casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
Layer half of onions; cover top with half of cheese.
Repeat.
Dot each layer with 3 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour chicken broth over all and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
